01:24.293 --> 01:27.336
Apollo dancing around
with his arms in the air.

01:37.639 --> 01:39.182
Five,

01:40.309 --> 01:42.014
six, seven,

01:43.270 --> 01:45.480
eight, nine...

01:52.613 --> 01:53.988
Come on!

01:55.115 --> 01:57.825
Apollo
can't believe it.

02:14.176 --> 02:17.762
The champion got a left to
the ribs, his right ribs.

02:25.562 --> 02:26.854
You okay, champ?

02:26.939 --> 02:28.231
Yeah, I'm okay.
I'm okay.

02:28.315 --> 02:29.565
Your rib's broken.

02:29.650 --> 02:30.817
He broke my ribs!

02:30.901 --> 02:34.195
I can't see nothing. Gotta
open my eye. Cut me, Mick.

02:34.279 --> 02:35.279
I don't want to do it!

02:35.364 --> 02:36.823
Go on, cut me.

02:36.907 --> 02:38.115
Cut me.

02:38.200 --> 02:39.992
Okay.
Try and cut it.

02:40.077 --> 02:42.495
You're bleeding inside, champ.
I'm gonna stop the fight.

02:42.579 --> 02:46.457
Hey, you ain't stopping nothing,
man. You ain't stopping nothing.

02:46.542 --> 02:48.334
You stop this fight,
I'll kill you!

02:48.418 --> 02:50.211
All right.
I won't stop it.

02:50.295 --> 02:51.879
I'm going!
You want to go...

02:51.964 --> 02:53.506
Last round!

02:53.590 --> 02:55.049
You gotta give it
your all!

02:55.133 --> 02:57.760
Get it off! You gotta
get him down in the body.

03:03.392 --> 03:06.435
There's the bell
for the 15th and final round.

03:09.815 --> 03:14.193
You better start fighting. You been
doing nothing. You been doing nothing.

03:14.278 --> 03:17.154
They look like they've
been in a war, these two.

03:17.239 --> 03:18.489
Come on over here.

03:25.873 --> 03:28.249
Apollo, the champion,
really tagged him.

03:28.333 --> 03:31.794
And Apollo clearly protecting
his right side, his ribs.

03:34.006 --> 03:35.131
Oh, look at that!

03:35.215 --> 03:36.299
Body punches!

03:37.509 --> 03:39.051
Hard left and right.

03:39.136 --> 03:40.553
Oh, look at the blood
coming out of his mouth.

03:40.637 --> 03:44.682
He's spitting up blood now.
He takes one to the head.

03:46.351 --> 03:48.477
A tremendous
right hand from Rocky.

03:49.146 --> 03:50.980
Go for it.
Go for it, Rock!

03:51.064 --> 03:52.231
Listen
to this crowd!

03:52.316 --> 03:53.482
Left to the ribs.

03:53.567 --> 03:57.403
Another to the ribs. That left
hand again. A right to the chin!

03:57.487 --> 04:02.033
He's got him up against the
ropes! Apollo, the champion...

04:04.745 --> 04:08.122
Ain't gonna be no rematch.
Ain't gonna be no rematch.

04:08.206 --> 04:10.541
Don't want one.

04:19.843 --> 04:20.843
There's chaos.

04:20.928 --> 04:22.553
Rocky, you went the distance.
You went the 15 rounds.

04:22.679 --> 04:23.930
How do you feel? All right. All right.

04:24.014 --> 04:26.057
What were you thinking about
when that buzzer sounded off?

04:26.141 --> 04:27.099
Adrian!
What did you think about

04:27.184 --> 04:28.434
in the 15th round
when you were coming out?

04:28.518 --> 04:29.894
Adrian!

04:29.978 --> 04:32.980
Rocky. Rocky.

04:35.692 --> 04:39.403
Rocky! Rocky!

04:39.488 --> 04:44.033
We have had the privilege of
witnessing the greatest exhibition

04:44.117 --> 04:48.120
of guts and stamina
in the history of the ring.

04:48.205 --> 04:49.997
Adrian!

04:50.958 --> 04:52.708
Rocky!

04:52.793 --> 04:53.793
Ladies and gentlemen...

04:53.877 --> 04:54.877
Rocky!

04:54.962 --> 04:58.214
...we have a split decision.

05:00.926 --> 05:02.551
Adrian!

05:02.636 --> 05:05.471
Eight for Apollo Creed!
Rocky!

05:07.891 --> 05:10.017
Those fans out
there deserve a rematch.

05:10.102 --> 05:12.186
Ain't gonna be no rematch.
Come on!

05:12.270 --> 05:16.148
I had enough things
in my face today! Adrian!

05:16.233 --> 05:19.902
Rocko!
That's my friend. Rocko!

05:19.987 --> 05:22.363
You're breaking my jacket.

05:22.447 --> 05:24.156
Paulie!

05:24.241 --> 05:25.324
Adrian!

05:25.409 --> 05:26.409
Rocky!

05:26.493 --> 05:27.493
Adrian!
Rocky!

05:27.577 --> 05:29.120
Hey, where's your hat?

05:29.204 --> 05:30.496
I love you!

05:30.580 --> 05:31.914
I love you.

05:35.585 --> 05:37.503
I love you!
I love you!

05:37.587 --> 05:39.422
I love you.

07:48.051 --> 07:49.718
Hey, Rock!
Hey, Rocky!

07:51.096 --> 07:53.013
Rocky Balboa!

07:53.098 --> 07:54.890
Get them
out of here!

07:54.975 --> 07:59.186
Let him breathe, will you? Give him air!

07:59.271 --> 08:01.897
Sit down, Rocky.
Sit down.

08:01.982 --> 08:03.065
Rocky, do you think you had it won?

08:03.150 --> 08:04.150
I don't know. I...

08:04.234 --> 08:06.318
How about
a statement, Rocky?

08:06.403 --> 08:08.529
I don't know.
I'm at a loss for words.

08:08.613 --> 08:09.822
Get back there!

08:09.906 --> 08:11.031
Rocky,
do you think you had it won?

08:11.116 --> 08:12.283
I don't know.

08:12.367 --> 08:13.534
Rocky, stay!

08:13.618 --> 08:14.785
Where's the doctor?

08:14.870 --> 08:16.871
How's my nose look?
As bad as Mickey's?

08:16.955 --> 08:18.998
It ain't that horrible.
Now give him a break.

08:19.082 --> 08:20.499
Just one more.
Get out of there.

08:20.584 --> 08:22.084
Rocky, is that the worst
beating you ever took?

08:22.169 --> 08:24.420
You! No, you're gonna get worse
if you don't get out of here.

08:24.504 --> 08:27.089
Rocky, what did you think
going into the last round?

08:27.174 --> 08:29.800
I don't know. That I should have
stayed in school or something.

08:29.885 --> 08:31.635
Rocky, do you think
you have brain damage?

08:31.720 --> 08:32.720
I don't see any.

08:32.804 --> 08:34.597
Where is he?
Where is he?

08:34.681 --> 08:36.765
Apollo,
how about a statement?

08:37.142 --> 08:39.101
Get away from me! How
about a statement, Apollo?

08:39.186 --> 08:41.437
Hey, Stallion! Stallion!

08:41.520 --> 08:43.355
You got a dull skull,
Stallion.

08:43.440 --> 08:46.317
You're lucky, so lucky.
What you did was a miracle.

08:46.401 --> 08:47.902
You're the luckiest man
on the face of the Earth.

08:47.986 --> 08:49.278
I want you to
know that, Stallion.

08:49.362 --> 08:50.487
Do I look lucky?

08:50.572 --> 08:52.448
Look, nobody goes
the distance with me.

08:52.532 --> 08:55.159
Get up out of that chair, chump, and
let's finish this fight right now.

08:55.243 --> 08:56.493
Apollo, don't, please.
Sit down.

08:56.578 --> 08:57.703
Is he serious?

08:57.787 --> 08:59.538
Were you going down? Did
the bell save you, Apollo?

08:59.623 --> 09:01.457
Bell nothing, man.
I can beat that chump.

09:01.541 --> 09:03.125
I'll fight him
any place, any time.

09:03.210 --> 09:04.418
Does that mean
there'll be a rematch?

09:04.502 --> 09:07.046
I said any place, any
time, man. Can you hear?

09:07.130 --> 09:09.840
Hey, yo, Apollo, you said there
weren't gonna be no rematch.

09:09.925 --> 09:11.550
Look, chump,
any place, any time.

09:11.635 --> 09:13.969
Rocky, a rematch
could be worth millions.

09:14.054 --> 09:15.596
Well, I'm officially
retired now.

09:15.680 --> 09:17.181
Don't you run out
on me now.

09:17.265 --> 09:18.307
Don't you run out
on me, Stallion.

09:18.391 --> 09:21.810
I gave you a shot the first time. Now
I'm ready to give you a second shot.

09:21.895 --> 09:24.563
He sure has a lot of energy. You
know, you got nothing to prove.

09:24.648 --> 09:28.901
I don't care what the hell them judges
said. This is the man that won the fight!

09:28.985 --> 09:32.279
I'm gonna show you how lucky you are!
You're gonna fight me again, chump!

09:32.364 --> 09:35.407
Come back here! Don't run out
on me! Come back here, Rock!

09:35.492 --> 09:36.700
Yo, Adrian?
Yes.

09:36.785 --> 09:38.869
You'd better go home
'cause I'm gonna be busy

09:38.954 --> 09:40.955
healing here for a while,
you know.

09:41.039 --> 09:42.581
I want to be here.

09:42.666 --> 09:44.792
No, maybe you better go home
with Paulie and get some sleep...

09:44.876 --> 09:48.212
Wait a minute.
Get some sleep, you know.

09:50.465 --> 09:52.508
I love you.
I love you.

09:52.592 --> 09:54.134
I love you. See you.

09:54.219 --> 09:55.719
See you later.
See you, Mick.

09:59.140 --> 10:01.100
Can you fix my nose?

10:01.184 --> 10:04.311
I'm a little depressed
about my nose.

10:04.396 --> 10:08.065
We'll fix that all right.
It's the eye that concerns me.

10:09.067 --> 10:10.693
The eye's great.

10:12.237 --> 10:15.072
I ain't never
really felt this good.

10:17.200 --> 10:19.576
You guys should've
seen us tonight.

10:21.037 --> 10:22.413
We did good.

10:23.707 --> 10:26.750
I almost won, you know...
You should've seen it.

10:29.462 --> 10:32.840
You had him in the 10th,
and in the 15th he was gone.

10:33.675 --> 10:34.967
You think so?

10:35.051 --> 10:36.260
Trust me.
I was there.

10:37.095 --> 10:39.013
How's your face,
Rock?

10:39.097 --> 10:40.639
I don't know.
How's it look?

10:41.725 --> 10:43.726
I wouldn't want it.

10:44.769 --> 10:47.938
Rocky, I got a little favor
I'd like to ask of you.

10:48.565 --> 10:51.734
You know, your friend Gazzo,
he admires you a lot.

10:52.736 --> 10:54.445
Tell him to give me
your old job with him.

10:54.529 --> 10:56.155
You mean collecting?

10:56.239 --> 10:57.323
Yeah, I'm good with numbers.

10:57.407 --> 10:58.407
Yeah.

10:59.409 --> 11:03.037
Okay. As soon as I get
finished, you know, healing here,

11:03.580 --> 11:07.249
I'll tell him to give
you my old job, okay?

11:07.334 --> 11:08.500
I'd appreciate that.

11:08.585 --> 11:10.419
What are you doing here?

11:11.087 --> 11:14.757
Visiting hours are over.
I have to ask you to leave.

11:16.176 --> 11:17.551
Now.

11:17.635 --> 11:18.927
Okay. See you later,
Paulie.

11:19.054 --> 11:22.056
Okay. Everybody's proud
of you, Rock. Yeah?

11:22.140 --> 11:23.766
Yeah.
Now.

11:23.850 --> 11:25.184
I feel good tonight.

11:25.268 --> 11:26.602
Yeah, you look good.

11:26.686 --> 11:27.936
Let's go.

11:31.149 --> 11:32.691
How are we feeling tonight?

11:32.776 --> 11:34.276
Oh, very handsome.

11:43.119 --> 11:44.870
That tastes good.

11:44.954 --> 11:46.622
My kid would die
for your autograph.

11:48.166 --> 11:49.208
Sure.

11:49.292 --> 11:50.250
Would you sign it,
please,

11:50.335 --> 11:52.878
"To my good friend,
Charlie Flynn. "

11:54.506 --> 11:55.631
My hands are so sore.

11:55.715 --> 11:56.799
It's okay.

12:01.971 --> 12:03.722
It's my first autograph.
Thank you.

12:03.807 --> 12:05.307
You're welcome.

12:11.314 --> 12:14.775
"To my good friend, Charlie
Flynn," who I don't even know.

12:22.784 --> 12:24.159
Yo, Apollo?

12:25.787 --> 12:27.246
Who is it?

12:27.330 --> 12:28.747
It's just me, Rocky.
Listen.

12:28.832 --> 12:31.166
Could you answer
me one question?

12:31.835 --> 12:33.085
Yeah, sure.

12:33.420 --> 12:35.462
Did you give me your best?

12:38.091 --> 12:39.174
Yeah. Yeah.

12:43.012 --> 12:44.346
Thank you.

12:56.568 --> 12:58.110
This coming year, you know,
Rocky. How you feeling?

12:58.194 --> 12:59.236
You all right?

12:59.320 --> 13:00.320
Yeah, I feel great
being outside.

13:00.405 --> 13:02.781
This coming year, you're
gonna make $300,000 with us.

13:02.866 --> 13:04.116
Yeah?
This fiscal year.

13:04.200 --> 13:05.451
Hey, Rock!

13:05.535 --> 13:06.785
Hey, how you doing,
Pete?

13:06.870 --> 13:08.454
Hey, could you sign
my head?

13:08.538 --> 13:09.580
Yeah, sure.

13:09.664 --> 13:10.789
Thanks.

13:10.874 --> 13:12.374
Hope it don't
go to your brain.

13:12.792 --> 13:14.626
Bet that's heavy.
A little bit.

13:14.711 --> 13:17.421
Yeah, well, just think how fast
you'll be when you get it off.

13:17.505 --> 13:18.714
Just a minute. Can I
borrow this? Thanks a lot.

13:18.798 --> 13:20.257
Let me use your
head for a minute, kid.

13:20.341 --> 13:22.217
Here, sign, Rocky.
It's a standard deal.

13:22.302 --> 13:24.219
Wait. I want to talk to you
a little bit about this here.

13:24.304 --> 13:25.554
It's a standard
deal...

13:25.638 --> 13:27.055
Just for talking
about shaving stuff?

13:27.140 --> 13:28.557
That's all you do.

13:28.641 --> 13:29.975
Sledgehammers, whatever. Batteries...

13:30.059 --> 13:31.810
We've got all kinds, of course,
all kinds of commercials,

13:31.936 --> 13:33.270
so it could be anything.
Like balls and baseballs?

13:33.354 --> 13:34.855
Yeah, you're gonna
make $300,000.

13:34.939 --> 13:36.690
You gotta strike now while
the iron's hot, you know.

13:36.774 --> 13:37.816
Yeah. 20 minutes, it's all over.

13:37.901 --> 13:38.984
Yeah, people kind
of forget, you know.

13:39.068 --> 13:40.110
The time is now,

13:40.195 --> 13:41.320
if you want to make a dollar. Right now.

13:41.404 --> 13:44.907
Here. Sign it here. It takes you two
seconds to sign. It's a standard deal.

13:44.991 --> 13:47.826
Okay, I tell you what, I'll sign
it, but I gotta go somewhere now.

13:47.911 --> 13:49.661
Where you going? What could
be more important than this?

13:49.746 --> 13:53.790
I just gotta do some things, but
I'll be back. I'll talk to you.

13:53.875 --> 13:55.042
Give me a call, then.

13:55.126 --> 13:56.251
Where will we call you?

13:56.336 --> 13:57.544
I'll give you a call.

13:57.629 --> 13:58.795
I call you.
You got a number?

13:58.880 --> 14:01.965
I'll just call you. I'll
go, "Hey! Yo!" I'll call you.

14:02.050 --> 14:03.800
Okay. All right,
you call. Here.

14:04.552 --> 14:06.637
The guy's got
brain damage.

14:08.181 --> 14:09.806
You know, it's great
being out of the hospital

14:09.891 --> 14:12.851
and not having to take all
those pills and everything.

14:12.936 --> 14:16.688
And my legs were getting so sore and
all that, you know, just laying there.

14:16.773 --> 14:21.735
I was kind of shrinking and all that.
It's great to be outside, you know?

14:23.488 --> 14:25.364
What are we doing
here at the zoo?

14:25.448 --> 14:28.325
Well, you know, I kind of
like the zoo a lot, you know.

14:28.409 --> 14:30.536
It's a special place,
especially when it snows,

14:30.620 --> 14:33.789
you know, it kind of smells clean
and everything like that, you know.

14:33.873 --> 14:36.166
Don't you like the zoo?
Huh?

14:36.251 --> 14:37.876
I like the zoo.

14:37.961 --> 14:39.127
Yeah, me, too.

14:41.965 --> 14:45.467
You know,
I was wondering, like,

14:45.552 --> 14:50.138
what do you think you're doing
for, like, the next 40 or 50 years?

14:50.223 --> 14:52.724
What do you mean?

14:57.146 --> 15:02.150
I was wondering if you wouldn't
mind marrying me very much.

15:03.736 --> 15:06.238
What'd you say?

15:07.282 --> 15:10.367
If you wouldn't mind
marrying me too much.

15:13.496 --> 15:16.873
Yes. I'd like
to marry you.

15:16.958 --> 15:19.167
Yeah?
Yes.

15:20.628 --> 15:22.129
Yeah?
Yes.

15:31.806 --> 15:35.809
I'll be a good guy, I promise.
I ain't gonna do nothing wrong.

15:35.893 --> 15:40.522
I ain't gonna leave no hair in the
sink or nothing like that, you know.

15:40.607 --> 15:43.817
Things are gonna be great,
you know that? Hey!

15:43.901 --> 15:47.154
Hey, we're getting married,
you know. You want to come?

15:47.238 --> 15:50.616
If you can get out for the weekend,
I'll send you an invitation, Mr. Tiger!

15:50.700 --> 15:52.701
That's fantastic,
ain't it?

16:08.551 --> 16:10.427
Yeah, absolutely.
Yes.

16:16.851 --> 16:18.727
I do.
Thanks.

16:25.109 --> 16:27.235
You may kiss the bride now.

16:28.571 --> 16:29.738
I gotta take this off?

16:29.822 --> 16:30.906
Yeah.

16:41.209 --> 16:43.835
Go in peace and God bless you.

16:43.920 --> 16:46.421
Thanks, Father. You done
real good. I'm proud of you.

16:46.506 --> 16:48.507
Okay. Things are
gonna be great.

16:48.591 --> 16:49.883
Rocky,
congratulations!

16:49.967 --> 16:53.011
Thanks a lot, thanks
a lot. Thanks, Tony.

16:53.096 --> 16:55.013
Hey, I ain't gonna need any
luck. Everything's gonna be okay.

16:55.098 --> 16:57.182
Hey, Rock, you want to
buy into the pet shop?

16:57.266 --> 16:59.643
Well, thanks, but I wanna
do commercials instead.

16:59.727 --> 17:01.019
Commercials? What for? Concussions?

17:01.104 --> 17:02.187
Yeah. Concussions.

17:02.271 --> 17:04.021
Rocky.
Yeah.

17:04.107 --> 17:07.567
Isn't that Father
something?

17:07.694 --> 17:09.694
Good luck to the both of
you. Thank you very much.

17:09.779 --> 17:11.696
Well, thanks, Mick.
I gotta go back to the gym.

17:11.781 --> 17:13.531
I got a couple
of good prospects.

17:13.616 --> 17:14.700
Yeah? Are they
really good?

17:14.784 --> 17:15.867
Yeah, they're
pretty good.

17:15.952 --> 17:18.203
All right. See you around,
Mick. Thanks for coming.

17:18.287 --> 17:19.538
Can we go
drink now?

17:19.622 --> 17:22.249
Excuse me, can I borrow the
bridegroom for one minute?

17:22.333 --> 17:24.209
You look beautiful, Adrian.

17:24.292 --> 17:26.169
Yeah, she really
turned out pretty.

17:26.253 --> 17:29.047
Now, listen, how much money
you make from your last fight?

17:29.132 --> 17:31.633
I mean, how much money
did you clear?

17:31.718 --> 17:32.884
About 37 grand.

17:32.969 --> 17:34.052
I know, taxes kill you.

17:34.137 --> 17:35.387
Hey, what do you wanna do
with your money now?

17:35.471 --> 17:37.848
You want to put
them on the street?

17:37.932 --> 17:40.058
Hey, Tony,
I just got married in here.

17:40.143 --> 17:41.685
I know,
and I'm happy for you.

17:41.769 --> 17:44.896
How's about investing in
condominiums? It's safe.

17:44.981 --> 17:46.022
Condominiums?

17:46.107 --> 17:47.858
Yeah, condominiums.

17:50.236 --> 17:52.237
I never use them.

18:22.351 --> 18:24.019
Hey, yo!
What are youse doing?

18:24.103 --> 18:26.605
Hey, Rock!
What's happening, man?

18:26.689 --> 18:29.107
Well, you know, I just got
a little married, you know.

18:29.192 --> 18:30.776
Hey, Rock,
congratulations!

18:30.860 --> 18:32.611
What are you guys doing?
Drinking some wine here?

18:32.695 --> 18:33.904
Yeah, man,
we're doing it.

18:33.988 --> 18:35.280
Keep singing some more.
I like that stuff.

18:35.364 --> 18:37.115
Okay, babe. Sing
something for him, Frank.

18:37.200 --> 18:42.954
There are two kinds of love
That you ought to know

18:43.039 --> 18:47.542
There are two kinds
of love

18:47.627 --> 18:49.711
There are two kinds of...

18:49.796 --> 18:50.921
Who are they?

18:51.005 --> 18:52.672
They're like the neighborhood's
