33:34.763 --> 33:36.764
That's bad manners,
ain't it, Adrian?

33:36.848 --> 33:37.848
Yes.

33:37.933 --> 33:42.561
I'll tell you, I gotta be almost punchy
to be doing this in front of my wife.

33:42.646 --> 33:46.982
You want to quit? Then
quit! Leave! Get out of here!

33:47.067 --> 33:49.276
I didn't want you for this
setup in the first place.

33:49.361 --> 33:51.737
You have wasted,
wasted our time, sir.

33:51.822 --> 33:53.781
This is a complete bust,
the whole afternoon.

33:53.865 --> 33:56.367
Leonard. Leonard,
where are you going?

33:56.451 --> 33:58.911
I want you to take
him with you, Leonard.

33:58.995 --> 34:01.247
Take this man with you.
He is not a professional.

34:01.331 --> 34:03.499
I only work
with professionals.

34:03.583 --> 34:06.460
You cost us thousands of
dollars because you can't read.

34:07.254 --> 34:10.715
"'It's no time to cuss
me,' snarled the robber.

34:10.799 --> 34:14.677
"'By God, fellows, grab your
rifles and take color... Cover. "'

34:14.761 --> 34:15.928
How does that sound?

34:16.388 --> 34:18.013
It's good.
Yeah?

34:18.306 --> 34:21.766
You know, being a good reader's gonna
help me get a good office job, you know?

34:21.851 --> 34:23.101
Want to hear some more?

34:23.186 --> 34:24.395
I can't wait.

34:25.981 --> 34:27.148
Okay.

34:27.815 --> 34:30.900
"'There ain't no cover,
Smokey,' said Brad Lincoln.

34:30.985 --> 34:32.652
"'We better head
for the canyon. "'

34:32.737 --> 34:34.196
You read nice.

34:34.281 --> 34:35.656
Thank you.
You lie nice.

34:35.741 --> 34:37.074
Thank you.

34:39.536 --> 34:42.246
And how far did you go in
high school, Mr. Balboa?

34:42.330 --> 34:43.581
Ninth.

34:43.665 --> 34:44.831
And one last question.

34:44.916 --> 34:47.168
Do you have
a criminal record?

34:48.754 --> 34:50.963
Nothing worth
bragging about.

34:53.800 --> 34:57.219
Would you be interested
in some sort of manual labor?

34:57.512 --> 35:00.389
Well, I got nothing against
honest manual labor.

35:00.474 --> 35:03.768
It's just that I'd like to see if
I could make a living sitting down,

35:03.852 --> 35:06.729
like you're doing
over there.

35:06.813 --> 35:10.399
Can I be honest? No one's going
to offer you an office job.

35:10.484 --> 35:14.278
There's too much competition.
Why don't you fight?

35:14.362 --> 35:17.406
I've read somewhere
you're a very good fighter.

35:18.742 --> 35:20.201
Yeah? Well...

35:21.703 --> 35:24.789
Was you ever punched in the
face 500 times a night, you know?

35:24.873 --> 35:27.416
Stings after a while,
you know.

35:30.212 --> 35:33.464
Thank you very much for
your time. I appreciate it.

35:43.934 --> 35:45.476
Mr. Balboa?
Yeah.

35:45.560 --> 35:47.645
I'm very sorry.
We have nothing.

35:47.729 --> 35:49.355
Are you sure?

35:49.439 --> 35:50.481
Next.

35:50.774 --> 35:52.775
Hey, look, pal,
you gotta be realistic.

35:52.859 --> 35:55.694
You got no high school
diploma, no qualifications.

35:55.779 --> 35:59.865
Wouldn't you be more content with
a good-paying menial labor job?

36:01.827 --> 36:03.035
Thanks.

36:04.579 --> 36:07.665
The way I see it is, I can get
another job if I want to, you know?

36:07.749 --> 36:11.961
But do I want to? Do I want to be doing
something I ain't gonna be happy doing?

36:12.045 --> 36:15.047
Plus, you know, we need
the money now, Butkus.

36:16.383 --> 36:18.467
Dogs don't want to
hear my problems.

36:18.552 --> 36:19.760
Come on.

36:20.846 --> 36:25.933
Yeah. I wish I was a canine
sometimes. Give me a kiss.

36:26.142 --> 36:28.894
The only job I
got is lugging beef.

36:28.979 --> 36:31.105
You got nothing better for
Rocky than hauling beef?

36:31.189 --> 36:33.357
Hey, that's all I got, and
we're cutting back, too.

36:33.441 --> 36:36.110
So, Rocky, if you want to work,
it'd be from week to week, okay?

36:36.194 --> 36:39.071
Well, that's okay with me,
but when can I start?

36:39.155 --> 36:40.823
Well, how about
tomorrow?

36:40.907 --> 36:42.533
Well, how about today?

36:43.702 --> 36:44.743
Okay. We got
a load coming in.

36:44.828 --> 36:45.828
Great.

36:45.912 --> 36:47.788
Hey, Paulie, you look
kind of skinny there, huh.

36:47.873 --> 36:49.707
Yeah, he's losing
weight, ain't he?

36:49.791 --> 36:51.542
Don't bother to
thank me.

36:51.626 --> 36:56.213
Hey, thanks a lot, Paulie, and you don't
have to thank me for the watch, either.

37:53.647 --> 37:55.147
Quitting time!

38:21.716 --> 38:24.718
Hey, there's the best-looking
thing I seen all day.

38:26.388 --> 38:27.680
You look tired.

38:27.764 --> 38:30.391
No, no. My face is tired. I feel okay.

38:30.475 --> 38:32.142
You want to take
a hot bath?

38:32.227 --> 38:34.353
No, come on. I feel dynamic. Honest.

38:34.437 --> 38:40.150
Hey, listen. Tomorrow... I was thinking at
work, maybe after work I'll take you out.

38:40.443 --> 38:43.487
You want to do something
nice, huh? You want to do that?

38:43.571 --> 38:45.280
I'd like to do that.
How's your stomach?

38:45.365 --> 38:47.032
All right.
You all right?

38:47.117 --> 38:49.535
You look great.
Do you know that?

39:44.257 --> 39:46.467
Hey, Rock, they just like old friends.

39:46.551 --> 39:48.385
Old friends never
tasted this good.

39:48.470 --> 39:50.054
I heard that.

40:00.148 --> 40:01.565
Yo!

40:01.900 --> 40:03.150
Yo, Rock!

40:05.153 --> 40:07.029
You wanted me, Frank?

40:07.280 --> 40:08.989
I gotta let you go.

40:12.285 --> 40:15.120
How come? I'm working
hard. I'm doing good.

40:15.205 --> 40:17.581
Yeah, real good, but we
gotta cut back on manpower

40:17.665 --> 40:21.126
and you ain't got enough
time in, you know? Seniority.

40:23.004 --> 40:26.131
How about if I take
a cut in pay, all right?

40:26.257 --> 40:28.342
Can't do it. Union rules.

40:29.928 --> 40:31.470
Union rules.

40:36.184 --> 40:37.351
Can I finish out
the day?

40:37.435 --> 40:38.519
Sure.

40:39.479 --> 40:41.522
Hey, Rocky, I'm sorry.

40:42.649 --> 40:44.108
Yeah, me, too.

40:52.325 --> 40:55.494
You got more stories than
a book, you know that?

40:55.578 --> 40:58.789
There's my brother-in-law,
Rocky. Give me the five.

40:59.833 --> 41:02.084
My brother-in-law
come to visit me.

41:02.710 --> 41:05.712
How you doing? How's everything
been? How's business? Okay?

41:05.797 --> 41:06.880
Yeah.

41:07.382 --> 41:08.507
Looking over your
old stomping ground?

41:08.591 --> 41:09.633
Yeah.

41:09.717 --> 41:12.511
Listen, Paulie, you want
to buy this car, you know.

41:12.595 --> 41:13.846
I thought
you liked it.

41:13.930 --> 41:15.347
It's okay, but I don't
need it no more.

41:15.431 --> 41:18.100
You know, I have a hard time making
these right turns with my bad eye.

41:18.184 --> 41:21.103
Keep hitting trash cans
and things like that.

41:21.312 --> 41:23.272
You got problems at home?
You need bread?

41:23.356 --> 41:24.731
No, no, everything's okay.
You know,

41:24.816 --> 41:28.026
this car would look great wrapped
around you, you know. Wouldn't it?

41:28.111 --> 41:31.321
Look, you need a hand-out,
I'll give you a hand-out.

41:31.406 --> 41:33.407
No, I don't need
no hand-out, Paulie.

41:34.033 --> 41:36.326
Look, you want
to buy the car?

41:36.411 --> 41:39.663
Sure. Why don't you be
smart and fight again?

41:42.584 --> 41:45.669
That's okay. I don't need to fight no
more. Listen, you want to buy the car?

41:45.753 --> 41:48.213
You want to pick up the
payments and all of that?

41:48.298 --> 41:49.923
Is my sister giving you
a hard time?

41:50.091 --> 41:51.925
You know, if she is,
you break her teeth.

41:53.928 --> 41:55.637
I appreciate the advice,
Paulie,

41:55.722 --> 41:57.848
but I kind of like her teeth,
you know, where they are.

41:57.932 --> 42:01.768
Okay? Here you go.
You bought yourself a car.

42:02.854 --> 42:06.607
Good car, you know. Gotta buckle
up for safety and all that.

42:08.234 --> 42:10.611
Where you going?
You need a lift?

42:11.988 --> 42:13.071
Nah.

42:14.532 --> 42:16.074
See you around.

42:23.917 --> 42:26.001
Hey,
say hi to my sister for me!

42:28.254 --> 42:31.632
Hey, listen, if you two
need the car, just ask!

42:44.729 --> 42:47.481
When did you get home?
I thought you were at work.

42:47.565 --> 42:50.317
No, I ain't at work
no more. I got...

42:51.986 --> 42:53.695
I got canned today.

42:56.532 --> 42:57.824
What happened?

42:57.909 --> 42:59.159
I don't know.
I was...

42:59.827 --> 43:02.329
You know, it's nobody's fault. They
were just cutting back, you know.

43:02.413 --> 43:03.664
It was economics.

43:05.041 --> 43:06.416
What are you gonna do?

43:06.501 --> 43:08.377
I don't know. I was

43:09.003 --> 43:11.004
thinking about fighting.

43:12.924 --> 43:16.260
What about your eye, you know? The
doctor said you shouldn't fight anymore.

43:16.344 --> 43:21.556
No, no. He recommended I don't
fight, and I recommend that I do.

43:22.433 --> 43:23.433
You'll go blind.

43:23.518 --> 43:25.936
Nobody's going blind.
Honest, I see great, you know.

43:26.020 --> 43:28.939
I see like a beagle
or something like that.

43:31.150 --> 43:33.860
You could be whatever you want to
be. You don't have to fight anymore.

43:35.280 --> 43:38.740
You know, I am a fighter, not
too good, but that's what I do.

43:39.701 --> 43:43.287
Oh, Rocky, you gave me your
word you wouldn't fight anymore.

43:43.371 --> 43:46.373
I mean, if we need money,
I could get a job.

43:50.253 --> 43:52.296
You don't have to do that.

43:53.756 --> 43:59.553
Oh, sure. I can get my job back,
you know, part-time, at the pet shop.

44:06.185 --> 44:08.979
But I'm the one
who's supposed to support.

44:10.023 --> 44:12.232
It's just for a little while.

44:15.445 --> 44:18.530
Listen, what if you catch some
pet shop disease or something?

44:18.614 --> 44:23.076
There are no pet shop diseases,
Rocky. I mean, really, I want to work.

44:24.912 --> 44:26.955
Do you really
want to do it?

44:28.541 --> 44:32.044
Yeah. We need the money.
It'll come in handy.

44:36.257 --> 44:38.759
Well, maybe you're right,
you know.

44:39.510 --> 44:41.803
You know what's best,
you know.

44:48.186 --> 44:50.187
Could you start dinner? I'm
starting to get a little hungry.

44:50.271 --> 44:52.856
I just want to finish
my workout here, okay?

44:52.940 --> 44:54.024
Sure.

45:17.006 --> 45:18.131
Jesus.

46:06.305 --> 46:08.098
Who the hell is that?

46:10.268 --> 46:12.227
Avon lady.

46:12.311 --> 46:14.187
Is that Rocky?

46:14.564 --> 46:18.400
Hey! I don't remember
giving you no key.

46:18.484 --> 46:21.778
Come on up here. Well,
the prodigal son returns!

46:21.863 --> 46:23.655
You don't look so bad,
do you, kid?

46:23.739 --> 46:26.116
What's that, an outer
space monster you brought?

46:26.200 --> 46:30.120
No, that's Butkus, my large dog.
What's that in your ear there?

46:30.204 --> 46:33.582
Oh, this? I hear
stupid things better.

46:34.292 --> 46:37.335
Well, now, did you come here
to show me that dog?

46:37.420 --> 46:40.505
No. Mick, can I have
my locker back?

46:40.590 --> 46:41.923
Yeah.
What's on your mind?

46:42.008 --> 46:43.008
Fighting.

46:43.593 --> 46:46.428
Fighting? What?
You want to go blind?

46:46.762 --> 46:48.138
Nobody's going blind.

46:48.222 --> 46:49.514
You heard what I said?

46:49.599 --> 46:52.184
Yeah, and the eye's great. No problem.

46:52.268 --> 46:55.312
Now, listen, every pug thinks
he has one good one left.

46:55.396 --> 46:58.773
Now forget it, 'cause your
fighting career is over, kid.

46:59.233 --> 47:00.317
Is that right?

47:00.401 --> 47:01.401
Yeah, I think
that's right.

47:01.486 --> 47:03.153
You know, I spend my whole
life getting a career.

47:03.237 --> 47:05.822
I get one, and you tell me it's over.

47:05.907 --> 47:08.450
What's the matter here?
You shook the hell out of

47:08.534 --> 47:10.410
the champion of
the whole wide world.

47:10.495 --> 47:11.828
You be happy with that.

47:11.913 --> 47:13.580
Well, maybe we can
do better this time.

47:13.664 --> 47:15.040
Or worse.
What about that?

47:15.124 --> 47:16.500
Hey, yo, Mick.

47:16.876 --> 47:21.087
I done you a favor last time, you
know. Can you do me one this time?

47:22.882 --> 47:24.883
I don't know.
You don't understand me.

47:24.967 --> 47:27.177
Now, look, I want to
show you something now.

47:27.261 --> 47:29.971
Test you. Now, look,
you look right there

47:30.097 --> 47:31.723
at the end of my nose, will you? Okay.

47:31.807 --> 47:32.891
I want to test you.

47:32.975 --> 47:34.017
Look at your nose.

47:34.101 --> 47:35.185
You look at my nose now.

47:35.269 --> 47:36.937
When I bring my finger in,
you tell me when you see it,

47:37.021 --> 47:38.647
will you?
Okay.

47:38.731 --> 47:40.023
There's the little thing.
I see it.

47:40.107 --> 47:41.233
That's good.

47:41.317 --> 47:42.859
I told you. It's okay.

47:42.944 --> 47:45.362
Now, wait.
Now we'll try the other lamp.

47:45.446 --> 47:48.198
Now, look here, will you?
Now, tell me.

47:52.286 --> 47:53.411
I see it.

47:53.496 --> 47:54.621
No, you see nothing.

47:54.705 --> 47:59.251
Creed would have caved in the whole
side of your face. Now, forget it, kid.

47:59.335 --> 48:03.672
You got the heart, but you ain't got
the tools no more. Now, forget it!

48:05.174 --> 48:06.216
Is that right?

48:06.300 --> 48:07.342
That is right.

48:07.426 --> 48:11.304
Yeah? Well, maybe it's you who
ain't got it no more, you know that?

48:11.389 --> 48:13.765
Yeah. Yeah. That's it.

48:17.436 --> 48:22.315
Now, look, you didn't even
see that coming, did you? No.

48:22.400 --> 48:26.027
Well, that was from
a broken-down pug like me.

48:26.112 --> 48:28.947
What do you think the champ
would do to you?

48:35.329 --> 48:37.289
I don't know.
Hurt me bad.

48:37.373 --> 48:39.833
No. He'd hurt you permanent.

48:39.917 --> 48:41.251
Permanent.

48:43.963 --> 48:45.755
You know, Mick, if...

48:48.676 --> 48:54.180
If I can't fight no more, maybe I
can help out around here, you know.

48:54.849 --> 48:58.310
Here? Well, sure, but...

48:58.436 --> 49:01.563
You know, you're
like royalty here, kid.

49:01.647 --> 49:05.025
You want those guys to see you
carrying towels and buckets around?

49:05.109 --> 49:06.901
Where's your dignity?

49:09.280 --> 49:11.990
I don't know how to
say this. I just...

49:14.243 --> 49:16.036
I gotta be around it.

49:23.169 --> 49:27.213
All right, kid.
Will you come back tomorrow?

49:32.511 --> 49:34.220
Thanks a lot, Mick.

49:57.411 --> 49:59.162
Look, I don't know
about anybody else,

49:59.246 --> 50:00.830
but as long as I'm gonna be
promoting this fight myself,

50:00.915 --> 50:03.291
I want a lot more pressure
put on for a rematch.

50:03.376 --> 50:07.253
Hey, we can get the same money
for the two top contenders.

50:07.338 --> 50:09.547
Why go after Balboa?
Why?

50:09.632 --> 50:12.842
Because there's still a lot of
people out there that think he won.

50:12.927 --> 50:15.804
There's a lot of people out there
accusing me of having the fight fixed,

50:15.888 --> 50:16.888
accusing me of being a fake,

50:16.972 --> 50:19.349
and insulting my kids
at school. That's why.

50:19.433 --> 50:20.517
You want to hear the truth?

50:20.601 --> 50:21.643
Yeah,
I want to hear the truth.

50:21.727 --> 50:24.979
The truth is that last time
he was damn lucky.

50:25.648 --> 50:27.232
Now he's all finished.

50:27.316 --> 50:30.360
I mean, he's been hanging around
doing nothing for six months.

50:30.444 --> 50:34.072
And any trainer worth anything
wouldn't have nothing to do with him.

50:34.156 --> 50:37.659
Now, I say, let's go after
some new meat.

50:37.743 --> 50:39.327
Forget this bum.

50:40.663 --> 50:43.665
Do you think I beat him
the last time? Do you?

50:45.418 --> 50:46.626
You got the decision.

50:46.711 --> 50:49.045
Man, I won,
but I didn't beat him!

50:50.798 --> 50:52.966
What are you afraid of, Tony?

50:54.468 --> 50:56.344
Honest?
Yeah, honest.

51:04.478 --> 51:06.604
He's all wrong for us,
baby.

51:07.523 --> 51:12.569
I saw you beat that man like I
never saw no man get beat before,

51:13.028 --> 51:16.656
and the man kept
coming after you.

51:18.367 --> 51:21.286
Now, we don't need that
kind of man in our life.

51:24.331 --> 51:26.458
I know what you're feeling.

51:28.002 --> 51:29.335
Let it go.

51:31.672 --> 51:32.964
Let it go.

51:34.008 --> 51:35.633
You're the champ.

51:39.346 --> 51:43.767
Thank you. Look, you're in charge
of my public relations, right?

51:43.851 --> 51:45.393
I want a whole new
campaign started.

51:45.478 --> 51:47.979
I want something done
publicly to bring this man out.

51:48.063 --> 51:49.773
I want something done
to jar this man's pride.

51:49.857 --> 51:52.692
I want something done to get
the people around him talking.

51:52.777 --> 51:54.110
All right?
You realize

51:54.195 --> 51:58.865
if we use this humiliation tactic,
you're setting yourself up as the bad guy.

51:59.200 --> 52:01.409
Look, man, whatever
gets him in the ring.

52:26.811 --> 52:28.728
What's happening?
Hey.

52:29.688 --> 52:31.648
What?
Where's your heart?

52:31.732 --> 52:33.107
What are you
talking about?

52:33.192 --> 52:34.484
You heard me.

52:34.568 --> 52:36.236
Well, what's this?

52:45.830 --> 52:48.248
It's kind of funny,
don't you think?

53:16.068 --> 53:18.611
Hey, hey, Chico,
listen. Hey, hey, listen.

53:18.696 --> 53:21.573
What's with the grin? How'd
you get so happy with yourself?

53:21.657 --> 53:24.701
Let me tell you something.
Snarl more, you see.

53:24.785 --> 53:29.205
Now, a good snarl can give you what
the Bible calls a psychological edge,

53:29.290 --> 53:33.376
because you snarl on your
punches. Wait a minute. Hey, Rock!

53:33.460 --> 53:38.381
Rock, come here a minute. Show this
Latin lamebrain how to snarl and punch.

53:38.465 --> 53:40.091
Show him that.

53:42.636 --> 53:45.763
That's it, you see. That's
ugly! That's a snarl.

53:46.265 --> 53:50.143
Hey, John, will you empty them buckets?
They're flowing over. Will you do that?

53:50.227 --> 53:51.686
Hey, Johnny, I'll do it.
No, let him do it.

53:51.770 --> 53:52.979
I got it, Rock.
Come on, I don't mind.

53:53.063 --> 53:54.105
Hey, Rock...

54:00.529 --> 54:02.280
Hey, wait a minute.

54:05.075 --> 54:06.701
Now you can
take it.

54:06.785 --> 54:07.994
Whoops.

54:08.078 --> 54:09.537
Hey!

54:09.622 --> 54:12.498
Can't you think of anything
tougher to say than, "Whoops"?

54:13.167 --> 54:15.126
Come on,
hit that right.

54:20.382 --> 54:23.343
Wait a minute, wait a minute.
Hold it. Hold it. Hold it. Hold it.

54:27.932 --> 54:29.766
All right. Come on.
Come on. Come on.

54:37.733 --> 54:39.025
Yo, Rock.

54:40.819 --> 54:42.904
Yo, Tony.
How you doing?

54:42.988 --> 54:45.239
How am I doing?
No, how are you doing?

54:45.324 --> 54:46.866
Look, I heard you was
working in this dump.

54:46.951 --> 54:48.952
Now what are you doing, huh?
Give it to me straight, brother.

54:49.036 --> 54:52.121
Oh, you know, I'm sweeping up,
making a few bucks here and there.

54:52.206 --> 54:56.292
You ain't no janitor, Rock. You don't need
a job like this. Besides, you're Italian.

54:56.377 --> 54:58.002
Now you come back
and work for me, Rock.

54:58.087 --> 54:59.754
Yeah, well,
what would I be doing?

54:59.838 --> 55:04.217
You mean, like, you know,
like collecting or something?

55:04.468 --> 55:07.971
Well, what else? Look, you come back.
You work on the docks, get some fresh air.

55:08.055 --> 55:09.347
It stinks in here.

55:09.431 --> 55:12.475
Yo, Tony,
I appreciate the offer, but...

55:13.268 --> 55:15.353
I can't do that
stuff no more.

55:15.437 --> 55:16.646
It's healthy, huh?

55:17.356 --> 55:20.066
Now, look, I gotta go.
Take it easy, huh, champ?

55:20.150 --> 55:22.944
Yeah. See you around.

55:24.154 --> 55:26.114
Remember that guy,
Rock?

55:47.970 --> 55:48.970
Yo!

55:50.097 --> 55:51.931
How's everybody in
the clubhouse tonight?

55:52.016 --> 55:53.599
Oh, fine.
How'd your day go?

55:53.684 --> 55:55.309
A million laughs.
You know, it was great.

55:55.436 --> 55:57.061
You need some help with that? Yes.

55:57.146 --> 55:58.855
Yes. Okay.

55:58.939 --> 56:00.106
Hey, you know, Adrian,
I was thinking

56:00.190 --> 56:02.483
maybe you ought to stay home
and rest your stomach, you know.

56:02.568 --> 56:04.861
Come on, Rock, it's just
part-time. We need the money.

56:04.945 --> 56:07.363
Yeah, well,
maybe you're right.

56:08.615 --> 56:10.033
There we go.

56:11.452 --> 56:13.703
That ain't my brand.
I like oatmeal.

56:13.787 --> 56:15.747
Hey, listen, why don't
we forget all this work?

56:15.831 --> 56:17.582
Listen, you want to
come home with me now,

56:17.666 --> 56:19.542
and maybe I'll tell you a
few jokes on the way home,

56:19.626 --> 56:21.544
and maybe you'll laugh,
you know?

56:22.129 --> 56:25.381
We need a few laughs in our
life. What do you think? Maybe?

56:25.466 --> 56:26.591
Yes.
Maybe?

56:26.675 --> 56:30.011
Maybe. Maybe? Okay.
Let's get out of here, okay?

56:30.095 --> 56:31.888
Okay.
Here we go.

56:31.972 --> 56:33.389
Hey, listen, Adrian.
Yeah.

56:33.474 --> 56:36.309
Listen to this one.
Why do cows wear bells?

56:37.227 --> 56:38.394
Why?

56:38.479 --> 56:39.645
'Cause their
horns don't work.

56:40.314 --> 56:42.231
Is that killing you?
No?

56:43.650 --> 56:44.650
Oh, God!

56:44.735 --> 56:46.235
They really used to
like it in third grade.

56:46.320 --> 56:50.198
I used to break everybody
up with that one.

56:52.534 --> 56:53.534
Yo!

56:54.995 --> 56:57.080
You really sweep good, man!

56:58.332 --> 57:00.666
Is he talking to you?

57:00.751 --> 57:04.545
Nah, he probably has me mixed
up with somebody else. Come on.

57:06.924 --> 57:08.508
Italian chicken.

57:10.677 --> 57:13.179
Boy,
you guys got the easy life.

57:13.847 --> 57:17.809
Hey, how you guys doing? Did
anybody move today, you know, huh?

57:17.893 --> 57:21.604
How's life in the bowl? You
gotta exercise once in a while.

57:22.231 --> 57:25.233
Would you like a little snacklet
or something? Here you go.

57:25.317 --> 57:28.861
Come on, Cuff. Hey, Link,
what, you drowning down there?

57:29.363 --> 57:33.199
Hey, want to hear some TV?
Want to hear some TV?

57:36.245 --> 57:40.456
The Los Angeles Rams. The Rams
defeated the Buccaneers in overtime,

57:40.541 --> 57:42.542
13 to 10, on Frank
Corell's 45-yard field goal.

57:42.626 --> 57:45.545
Hey, Butkus. Come here,
Butkus. Come here, boy.

57:47.172 --> 57:49.173
What did you do today,
huh?

57:50.134 --> 57:51.884
Did you bark at
anybody today?

57:51.969 --> 57:56.597
Yo, Adrian! Sometimes I look at Butkus
and I don't think he's a normal canine.

57:57.349 --> 57:58.349
Well, what do you
think he is?

57:58.433 --> 57:59.433
I don't know.

57:59.518 --> 58:02.019
He just don't look like a
regular dog to me sometimes,

58:02.104 --> 58:03.938
you know, when I look
inside there.

58:04.022 --> 58:07.942
Earlier today I was down at
Apollo Creed's palatial gym,

58:08.026 --> 58:12.905
and, as usual, the world champion was not
at a loss for words about Rocky Balboa.

58:12.990 --> 58:15.700
Look, I know a lot of people out
there want to see me in a rematch

58:15.784 --> 58:18.828
with a timid fellow who calls
himself the Italian Stallion.

58:18.912 --> 58:21.789
But this man does not have the honor to
meet me in the ring. Or is it Scallion?

58:21.915 --> 58:23.499
Now, listen, in fairness,
Apollo... What's his name?

58:23.584 --> 58:24.834
What is your name?

58:24.918 --> 58:26.085
...Rocky Balboa did
officially retire.

58:26.170 --> 58:29.005
Yeah. The bum's hiding. The bum's
running. He doesn't want to face me.

58:29.089 --> 58:30.423
He's scared.
You know it and I know it.

58:30.507 --> 58:32.508
Apollo, I think there's
more here than meets the eye.

58:32.593 --> 58:36.012
You've been under close scrutiny ever
since that split-decision victory.

58:36.096 --> 58:39.682
A lot of reporters, Apollo, including
me, thought it was an even draw.

58:39.766 --> 58:41.517
That's your opinion
and you're entitled to it.

58:41.602 --> 58:43.519
But now I'm ready
to have a rematch,

58:43.604 --> 58:46.522
to prove that this lucky club
fighter, and that's what he was, lucky,

58:46.607 --> 58:48.065
does not have the skill

58:48.150 --> 58:51.402
to last five minutes in the ring
with a superior athlete like me.

58:51.486 --> 58:54.447
The man's running, the man's hiding.
The man doesn't want to face me.

58:54.531 --> 58:57.366
So I say to you, Rocky Balboa,
or whatever your name is,

58:57.451 --> 58:58.868
that I want
the American people to know,

58:58.952 --> 59:00.369
I want
the whole world to know,

59:00.454 --> 59:02.455
that I'm ready, willing, and
able to meet you anywhere.

59:02.539 --> 59:05.541
Any place, any time, I will meet
and defeat this so-called fighter,

59:05.626 --> 59:07.668
who calls himself
the Italian Stallion,

59:07.753 --> 59:09.378
if the man only has the guts
to give me a call.

59:09.463 --> 59:12.423
And you can call me collect.
Call me, Balboa!

59:13.258 --> 59:16.427
This would be a legitimate rematch,
the boxer against the puncher,

59:16.511 --> 59:19.680
and I think everyone wants to see
them back in the ring together.

59:19.765 --> 59:23.351
But there's only one problem,
where is Rocky Balboa?

59:24.561 --> 59:25.811
Ugly bum!

59:34.488 --> 59:36.822
You know,
I was thinking that

59:37.991 --> 59:40.743
I ain't supposed to
do no commercials and

59:40.827 --> 59:43.621
I ain't supposed to
work in no meat house.

59:44.081 --> 59:46.290
I'm supposed to be
a fighter.

59:47.084 --> 59:48.876
But you gave that up.

59:49.962 --> 59:51.087
Yeah.

59:52.005 --> 59:54.799
I think I'm becoming
a nobody again, too.

59:55.133 --> 59:57.093
In whose eyes?
Not mine.

59:57.177 --> 59:58.511
In mine.

59:59.638 --> 01:00:00.846
In here.

01:00:03.850 --> 01:00:04.934
We'll get by.

01:00:05.018 --> 01:00:06.102
That's just it.

01:00:07.771 --> 01:00:11.107
I don't want you to get by
the hard way, you know?

01:00:11.191 --> 01:00:12.942
I want you to have
good things.

01:00:13.026 --> 01:00:15.319
I want the kid to
have good things.

01:00:15.404 --> 01:00:16.946
We'll have them.

01:00:18.198 --> 01:00:20.950
I just think we need
them now, don't you?

01:00:22.202 --> 01:00:23.786
Rocky, please...

01:00:24.871 --> 01:00:27.248
You don't have
to prove anything.

01:00:28.917 --> 01:00:30.876
Adrian, it's all I know.

01:00:32.462 --> 01:00:34.505
I don't want you to do it.

01:00:36.341 --> 01:00:37.925
It's all I know.

01:00:41.388 --> 01:00:42.638
Adrian?

01:00:45.183 --> 01:00:46.434
You know,

01:00:49.146 --> 01:00:52.356
I never asked you to stop
being a woman, you know?

01:00:53.233 --> 01:00:58.446
Please, I'm asking you, please,
don't ask me to stop being a man.

01:00:59.323 --> 01:01:00.531
Please.

01:01:31.146 --> 01:01:34.357
I think we ought to
knock his block off.

01:01:34.441 --> 01:01:35.524
Absolutely.

01:01:35.609 --> 01:01:36.734
Rocky.

01:01:40.155 --> 01:01:41.489
I'm sorry.

01:01:49.122 --> 01:01:51.123
Well...
Let's do it.

01:01:53.919 --> 01:01:57.213
Apollo! Has a site been
chosen for the rematch?

01:01:57.297 --> 01:01:59.715
This fight will be held in
the Philadelphia Spectrum,

01:01:59.800 --> 01:02:02.051
'cause I want this man's
hometown to see this.

01:02:02.302 --> 01:02:05.054
I want all of Philadelphia,
I want all of America,

01:02:05.138 --> 01:02:08.891
I want the whole world to see me
destroy this man after two short rounds.

01:02:08.975 --> 01:02:10.017
Because after this fight,

01:02:10.102 --> 01:02:12.520
he's gonna have to donate what's
gonna be left of his body to science.

01:02:12.604 --> 01:02:14.605
But there won't be much.
That I can guarantee you.

01:02:14.689 --> 01:02:19.068
Rocky, what do you think about the
fight taking place in the Spectrum?

01:02:19.152 --> 01:02:20.694
Well, I'm very happy
about that.

01:02:20.779 --> 01:02:21.904
Why?

01:02:21.988 --> 01:02:24.865
Well, it's only about 10 minutes
from my house, the Spectrum.

01:02:25.283 --> 01:02:27.827
Apollo, a lot of people say
that you lost the first fight,

01:02:27.911 --> 01:02:29.703
a victim of
the southpaw jinx.

01:02:29.788 --> 01:02:31.414
Did fighting a
left-hander throw you off?

01:02:31.498 --> 01:02:33.082
Southpaw jinx nothing!

01:02:33.166 --> 01:02:36.502
Last time, I took the fight too lightly,
and this man was just plain lucky.

01:02:36.586 --> 01:02:40.172
But this time... This time you
all will see the real Apollo Creed.

01:02:40.257 --> 01:02:42.591
The world is gonna see
the real Apollo Creed.

01:02:42.676 --> 01:02:46.595
Lightning fast and hard to catch.
No playing, no jiving, just business.

01:02:46.680 --> 01:02:48.222
All right. Looks like
he's got a good chance.

01:02:48.306 --> 01:02:53.269
Rocky, do you think you have a
chance this time against Apollo?

01:02:53.353 --> 01:02:55.896
I don't know.
He looks pretty mad.

01:02:57.107 --> 01:02:59.442
Me and Mick,
we're gonna try our best.

01:02:59.526 --> 01:03:01.902
His lungs he's
gonna punch out.

01:03:02.070 --> 01:03:03.904
Now, who's that?
Al Capone?

01:03:03.989 --> 01:03:05.406
I wouldn't sweat you.

01:03:06.575 --> 01:03:10.119
Look here, look here, a lot of people
may not like me, and that's okay.

01:03:10.203 --> 01:03:14.165
But come November, Apollo Creed will
provide the ultimate gala spectacle,

01:03:14.249 --> 01:03:17.501
on Thanksgiving, in front
of this man's home crowd.

01:03:17.586 --> 01:03:19.837
I'm gonna drop him
like a bad habit.

01:03:19.921 --> 01:03:21.964
Rocky, your pay for the
fight is very substantial.

01:03:22.048 --> 01:03:24.300
What are you gonna
do with the money?

01:03:24.384 --> 01:03:28.679
Well, the first thing I gotta do
is I gotta pay the rent, you know.

01:03:28.763 --> 01:03:31.682
And then, well, I made
this list on the way over.

01:03:31.766 --> 01:03:32.975
I was just thinking
of things to do.

01:03:33.059 --> 01:03:36.312
I'd like to get a couple
of hats, and a motorcycle,

01:03:36.396 --> 01:03:40.274
and a couple of quarts of perfume
for Adrian. She likes to smell good.

01:03:40.358 --> 01:03:44.987
And some Muppet toys. You know,
Ernie and Big Bird and that frog.

01:03:45.071 --> 01:03:47.198
What's his name?
Kermit or something?

01:03:47.282 --> 01:03:48.824
I don't know.

01:03:50.035 --> 01:03:51.911
And I thought maybe
a statue for the church,

01:03:51.995 --> 01:03:54.497
and I think a snow cone
machine for you, Paulie.

01:03:54.581 --> 01:03:56.207
You like snow cones,
don't you?

01:03:56.333 --> 01:03:57.333
Yeah.

01:03:57.417 --> 01:04:00.961
Rocky, got anything derogatory
to say about the champ?

01:04:01.087 --> 01:04:03.923
"Derogatory"?
Yeah. He's great.

01:04:04.007 --> 01:04:06.008
How about some clowning shots, Apollo?

01:04:06.092 --> 01:04:07.343
Yeah.

01:04:07.427 --> 01:04:10.262
Does this look like
a circus to you, man?

01:04:11.515 --> 01:04:13.724
Come November,
you're mine.

01:04:16.645 --> 01:04:17.853
He's very upset.

01:04:17.938 --> 01:04:19.146
Well...

01:04:23.443 --> 01:04:26.070
See how smooth
he moves there?

01:04:26.154 --> 01:04:28.030
See how he pumps
that jab into your eye?

01:04:28.114 --> 01:04:29.323
Yeah.

01:04:29.991 --> 01:04:33.160
You got guts to go back
in the ring with him, kid.

01:04:33.245 --> 01:04:35.204
Thanks a lot, Mick.

01:04:36.581 --> 01:04:39.792
Your style's too
easy to figure out.

01:04:39.876 --> 01:04:42.211
I mean, left-handed fighters
they're the worst, you know.

01:04:42.295 --> 01:04:44.129
They lead with
their face mostly.

01:04:44.214 --> 01:04:47.758
Trying to throw that big
left. Right's no damn good.

01:04:48.552 --> 01:04:50.970
They ought to
outlaw southpaws.

01:04:51.054 --> 01:04:53.389
Yeah, why didn't you
tell me this before?

01:04:53.473 --> 01:04:56.475
I didn't want to hurt
your feelings. Now, look.

01:04:57.435 --> 01:05:01.647
To pull this miracle off,
you gotta change everything.

01:05:01.731 --> 01:05:03.899
You gotta learn to be
a right-handed fighter.

01:05:03.984 --> 01:05:07.945
Now, this will confuse Apollo,
and it'll protect that bad eye.

01:05:09.030 --> 01:05:11.657
I can't learn how to
fight right-handed no more.

01:05:11.741 --> 01:05:16.078
What's "can't"? There ain't no
"can'ts"! There's no "can'ts. "

01:05:16.162 --> 01:05:19.748
Now, he will beat you uglier
than you are now.

01:05:19.833 --> 01:05:22.418
Now, listen, you start
fighting right-handed,

01:05:22.502 --> 01:05:24.128
and then you change
suddenly,

01:05:24.212 --> 01:05:27.715
and that'll make history,
but first you gotta get speed.

01:05:27.799 --> 01:05:33.721
Demon speed. Speed's what we
need. We need greasy, fast speed!

01:05:34.347 --> 01:05:37.683
Now, I'll show you a trick how
to get some speed in them legs.

01:05:37.767 --> 01:05:39.727
Do you have to wear
that stinking sweatshirt?

01:05:39.811 --> 01:05:41.312
Well, it brings me luck,
you know.

01:05:41.396 --> 01:05:43.272
You know what it brings?
It brings flies.

01:05:43.356 --> 01:05:45.149
Now, listen, I want you
to try... Listen to me.

01:05:45.233 --> 01:05:48.485
I want you to try to
chase this little chicken.

01:05:48.570 --> 01:05:51.363
Well, what do I gotta chase a chicken
for? It's embarrassing, you know.

01:05:51.448 --> 01:05:53.282
First,
because I said so.

01:05:53.366 --> 01:05:57.036
And second, because chicken-chasing
is how we always used to train

01:05:57.120 --> 01:05:58.203
in the old days.
Yeah.

01:05:58.288 --> 01:06:01.457
You catch this thing, you can
catch greased lightning. Ready?

01:06:01.541 --> 01:06:04.793
Yeah, well, I'd rather eat it than chase it.
It ain't very mature. Well, if you say so.

01:06:04.878 --> 01:06:08.297
Well, neither are you very mature!
Now, listen, get this thing.

01:06:08.381 --> 01:06:09.673
I'm a fighter.
I ain't a farmer.

01:06:09.758 --> 01:06:11.884
Come on at it!
Go on and get him!

01:06:11.968 --> 01:06:16.513
Get him! Get him! Get him! Come on!
What's the matter with you? Get him!

01:06:16.598 --> 01:06:19.224
Pick him up!
Pick him up!

01:06:19.309 --> 01:06:21.101
Pull him round!

01:06:22.270 --> 01:06:24.188
What's the matter?
You're so fast.

01:06:24.272 --> 01:06:26.815
Are you standing still or
something? Speed! Speed!

01:06:26.900 --> 01:06:29.610
Can't you catch
a little chicken?

01:06:29.694 --> 01:06:33.280
Come on! Move your tail!
Move your tail!

01:06:33.365 --> 01:06:36.367
You look like a girl out there.
What's the matter with you?

01:06:36.451 --> 01:06:38.744
I feel like
a Kentucky fried idiot.

01:06:40.163 --> 01:06:44.375
Wake up, will you? Would you wake up?
Come on. Come on. Give it. Give it.

01:06:44.459 --> 01:06:47.252
Yo, Rock. What's the matter
with my sister?

01:06:47.337 --> 01:06:49.296
Well, boy, I wish you'd go talk to her.

01:06:49.381 --> 01:06:52.007
You know, Adrian don't like this none.
She's started crying and everything.

01:06:52.092 --> 01:06:53.050
She don't like
me fighting.

01:06:53.134 --> 01:06:55.511
What's with this
domestic stuff?

01:06:55.595 --> 01:06:59.181
Tend to the business, will
you? Jab that till it hurts!

01:06:59.265 --> 01:07:03.018
Five hundred times without
stopping. Do you hear me? 500 times.

01:07:03.103 --> 01:07:04.770
Hey, Mick, I want to use my other arm.

01:07:04.854 --> 01:07:06.480
If you do,
I'm gonna chop it off.

01:07:06.564 --> 01:07:07.731
Is that clear?

01:07:07.816 --> 01:07:08.982
I'll figure something.

01:07:09.067 --> 01:07:11.819
Yeah, I wish you would, Paulie.
I appreciate it, you know.

01:07:11.945 --> 01:07:13.821
I'm sorry. Are you finished? Yeah.

01:07:13.905 --> 01:07:16.240
Can we go to work?
That would be nice.

01:07:16.324 --> 01:07:20.577
Now, hit that bag. Hit it.
Jab it till it hurts. Go ahead.

01:07:20.662 --> 01:07:22.037
Three, four...

01:07:22.122 --> 01:07:25.833
Yeah, I want
500 high ones. Go!

01:07:25.917 --> 01:07:27.376
Where was I?
Seven or eight?

01:07:30.505 --> 01:07:34.049
One, two. One, two. One,
two. Come on. Turn it over.

01:07:34.134 --> 01:07:39.805
Come on. Snap it. Come
on. Come on. Dig! Dig! Dig!

01:07:40.306 --> 01:07:41.557
All right,
pick it up.

01:07:42.475 --> 01:07:47.730
Come on. Pick them up. Pick
them up. Faster! Faster! Faster!

01:07:47.814 --> 01:07:49.815
Come on!
Faster!

01:07:57.699 --> 01:07:58.991
Time!

01:08:04.873 --> 01:08:05.998
Time!

01:08:11.296 --> 01:08:14.548
Get up! Get me another one, all right?

01:08:14.632 --> 01:08:17.134
Come on. You gotta ease up
on these sparring partners.

01:08:17.218 --> 01:08:18.385
You just get me another,
man.

01:08:25.727 --> 01:08:30.354
Time! What's the matter?
That bag too fast for you?

01:08:40.700 --> 01:08:43.118
You're gonna pound that
sass right out of him.

01:08:43.203 --> 01:08:47.747
Last time we should have won, but
this time you're gonna be scary, kid.

01:08:47.832 --> 01:08:51.877
You're gonna be a greasy,
fast, Italian monster!

01:08:51.961 --> 01:08:53.754
You're gonna eat lightning!

01:08:53.837 --> 01:08:55.589
You're gonna crap thunder!

01:08:55.673 --> 01:08:58.509
We'll have to put
you in a cage, kid.

01:09:00.636 --> 01:09:02.345
Let's take a break,
Mick, all right?

01:09:02.430 --> 01:09:04.096
Break? What break?

01:09:04.182 --> 01:09:06.390
Where are you going?
We're not finished.

01:09:06.475 --> 01:09:08.977
Hey, I said where
the hell you going?

01:09:09.062 --> 01:09:11.104
I'm talking to myself.

01:09:48.350 --> 01:09:50.894
Speed! Speed!

01:09:50.979 --> 01:09:53.145
Catch that punk!

01:09:53.231 --> 01:09:57.860
Speed, damn it, speed! Can't
you catch that little squirt?

01:09:57.944 --> 01:10:01.488
Can't you? Get off your
rear! Get the lead out!

01:10:01.573 --> 01:10:03.407
Move. Move! Fast!

01:10:03.491 --> 01:10:07.119
You look dead out there. If you
can catch that little speedball,

01:10:07.203 --> 01:10:09.371
you're gonna
catch Creed easy.

01:10:09.455 --> 01:10:11.373
Come on! Move! Move!

01:10:11.457 --> 01:10:13.542
All right. Time!

01:10:13.626 --> 01:10:16.128
Hey, dead ass.
Get over here.

01:10:18.298 --> 01:10:20.632
Hey, you sick, kid?

01:10:21.384 --> 01:10:24.303
Kid, what's the matter
with you?

01:10:24.387 --> 01:10:25.804
Nothing.

01:10:25.889 --> 01:10:27.890
Let me tell you
something, kid.

01:10:27.974 --> 01:10:30.475
Now, for a 45-minute fight,

01:10:30.602 --> 01:10:34.897
you gotta train hard
for 45,000 minutes.

01:10:34.981 --> 01:10:40.485
Forty-five thousand. That's 10 weeks.
That's 10 hours a day. You listening?

01:10:40.570 --> 01:10:43.071
And you ain't
even trained one.

01:10:43.156 --> 01:10:46.950
I don't know what the hell you're
waiting for. What are you waiting for?

01:10:47.035 --> 01:10:49.077
I don't know.

01:10:49.162 --> 01:10:51.163
Suit yourself.

01:10:52.624 --> 01:10:54.416
Yo, Rocky.

01:10:54.500 --> 01:10:56.919
Hey, yo, Paulie.
How you doing?

01:10:57.003 --> 01:10:58.462
I'm worried about you.
I've been watching.

01:10:58.546 --> 01:10:59.588
What?

01:10:59.672 --> 01:11:01.673
Your head ain't
screwed on right.

01:11:01.758 --> 01:11:04.801
Nah, come on. I'm doing okay.
You know, I've been thinking.

01:11:04.886 --> 01:11:06.762
You know, would you like
to work my corner?

01:11:06.846 --> 01:11:09.264
Want to get involved
in this fight, you know?

01:11:09.349 --> 01:11:11.683
Get involved in what?
Watching you get murdered?

01:11:11.768 --> 01:11:13.518
Oh, come on.
I'm doing okay.

01:11:13.603 --> 01:11:17.022
Come on. My sister got you so guilty,
you're running all over the place.

01:11:17.106 --> 01:11:18.357
She'll be all right.

01:11:18.441 --> 01:11:19.608
It ain't all right.

01:11:19.692 --> 01:11:21.985
Hey, Paulie, it's okay,
all right?

01:11:22.070 --> 01:11:23.445
It's not okay.

01:11:23.529 --> 01:11:25.697
Just leave Adrian alone,
all right?

01:11:36.834 --> 01:11:39.044
Hey, kid,
carry this, will you?

01:11:39.128 --> 01:11:42.631
Because I liked you better
when you was carrying spit.

01:11:42.715 --> 01:11:44.132
What's that supposed
to mean?

01:11:44.217 --> 01:11:46.259
It means that you're training
like a ninth-rate pug

01:11:46.344 --> 01:11:47.970
who ought to be pumping gas
in Jersey someplace.

01:11:48.096 --> 01:11:50.430
Yeah? Yeah, that's what it means.

01:11:50.515 --> 01:11:52.432
I think I'm gonna go
take a shower, Mick.

01:11:52.517 --> 01:11:54.393
That's a good idea.

01:11:54.811 --> 01:11:57.854
Soak your head someplace.
Soak it good.

01:12:06.406 --> 01:12:08.699
Yo, Adrian! Where are you?

01:12:08.783 --> 01:12:09.992
Paulie.

01:12:10.076 --> 01:12:12.494
Yeah, Paulie.
What the hell you doing?

01:12:12.578 --> 01:12:13.704
What do you mean?

01:12:13.788 --> 01:12:14.871
What the hell you doing?

01:12:14.956 --> 01:12:16.707
About what?

01:12:16.791 --> 01:12:18.792
About messing up
that guy over there.

01:12:20.420 --> 01:12:22.921
Don't start with me, Paulie.
I'm just trying to keep him safe.

01:12:23.006 --> 01:12:25.799
Yeah, what? Feeding
these goddamn squirrels?

01:12:25.883 --> 01:12:29.344
Did I teach you how to do that?
Ditching the guy when he needs your help?

01:12:29.429 --> 01:12:31.013
I can't believe
my ears.

01:12:31.097 --> 01:12:32.681
You didn't teach
me anything, Paulie.

01:12:32.765 --> 01:12:34.850
You didn't teach me anything,
and I never hurt Rocky.

01:12:34.934 --> 01:12:36.810
You're messing up his brain
real bad. You know that?

01:12:36.894 --> 01:12:37.936
That's not what I'm doing.

01:12:38.021 --> 01:12:39.104
I don't know what
you're talking about.

01:12:39.188 --> 01:12:40.230
Yeah, don't tell me!

01:12:40.314 --> 01:12:42.190
He's gonna get
hurt because of you!

01:12:42.275 --> 01:12:43.358
It's not true.

01:12:43.443 --> 01:12:44.526
Don't say that!

01:12:44.610 --> 01:12:45.694
I'm saying it.

01:12:45.778 --> 01:12:47.070
Come across and tell
him it's all right.

01:12:47.155 --> 01:12:48.405
It's not all right,
Paulie.

01:12:48.489 --> 01:12:52.492
If he goes blind, you walk away.
I can't. I love him. You don't!

01:12:58.041 --> 01:13:00.709
What are you doing?

01:13:00.793 --> 01:13:04.963
What are you doing? What's
wrong? Adrian, what's the matter?

01:13:08.885 --> 01:13:11.219
Come on.
Where are your guts?

01:13:11.304 --> 01:13:13.263
What's your problem,
Mick?

01:13:13.347 --> 01:13:15.223
My problem?
Yeah.

01:13:15.308 --> 01:13:19.061
You got the problem, kid.
You got a ticker problem.

01:13:19.145 --> 01:13:21.813
What's the matter? You
got nothing left inside?

01:13:21.898 --> 01:13:25.650
'Cause you're training like
a damn bum, you know that?

01:13:25.735 --> 01:13:27.736
Bum?
A bum.

01:13:29.489 --> 01:13:32.240
Maybe you're right. Maybe
I ain't got it no more.

01:13:32.325 --> 01:13:37.079
All right. Then don't you waste
my time no more. You hear that?

01:13:37.163 --> 01:13:40.165
Go away! Go back to the
docks where you belong.

01:13:40.249 --> 01:13:43.752
You go back to
being a two-bit nothing!

01:13:43.836 --> 01:13:49.091
But don't you ever come back here again,
because I'm too old to waste my time

01:13:49.175 --> 01:13:52.511
trying to train a no-good
loser like you, you bum!

01:13:52.595 --> 01:13:54.179
Hey, Rock, they want
you across the street.

01:13:54.263 --> 01:13:57.140
What's the matter?
Your wife's sick.

01:14:06.359 --> 01:14:08.944
Mr. Balboa?
I'm Dr. Cooper.

01:14:09.028 --> 01:14:12.030
The baby is fine, even
though it's a month premature.

01:14:12.115 --> 01:14:14.032
What is it?
It's a boy.

01:14:14.117 --> 01:14:15.951
Holy smoke. I didn't
know she could do it.

01:14:16.035 --> 01:14:18.703
Yeah, well, how is
Adrian? Where is Adrian?

01:14:18.788 --> 01:14:21.123
She's had complications.

01:14:22.959 --> 01:14:24.292
Like what?

01:14:24.377 --> 01:14:26.795
Your wife was hemorrhaging
when she was brought in.

01:14:26.879 --> 01:14:31.299
The premature delivery was most
likely caused by straining or overwork,

01:14:31.384 --> 01:14:35.554
and the sudden loss of blood has
caused her to slip into a coma.

01:15:05.585 --> 01:15:07.586
Adrian, it's me.

01:15:14.760 --> 01:15:17.846
They said outside
you're very sick, but I...

01:15:18.806 --> 01:15:21.099
I don't want to
believe that.

01:15:23.436 --> 01:15:25.896
Maybe you're just tired,
you know.

01:15:29.609 --> 01:15:35.113
Don't worry about nothing. You just
sleep as long as you want, okay?

01:15:35.198 --> 01:15:38.074
And I'm gonna be
here when you wake up.

01:15:47.084 --> 01:15:49.461
Rocky, come on. You're
not doing any good here.

01:15:49.545 --> 01:15:50.712
No, I can't...

01:15:50.796 --> 01:15:52.881
Let's go see the kid.
Adrian would want it.

01:15:52.965 --> 01:15:55.300
No. We gotta see
him together.

01:15:56.552 --> 01:15:59.596
It's okay. We gotta
see him together.

01:16:14.153 --> 01:16:17.822
Mr. Balboa,
visiting hours are over.

01:16:18.824 --> 01:16:21.159
Can't I stay?
I'll be quiet.

01:16:22.745 --> 01:16:25.664
I'm sorry.
Hospital rules.

01:16:28.000 --> 01:16:30.460
I can't do any more
of this watching stuff.

01:16:37.385 --> 01:16:39.386
Do you have a chapel?

01:16:40.304 --> 01:16:42.305
Yes, we do.

01:16:50.523 --> 01:16:52.524
Good night.

01:17:15.381 --> 01:17:17.382
Rock,

01:17:19.010 --> 01:17:21.011
it's 3:00 in the morning.

01:17:23.681 --> 01:17:28.143
You know that I
went up to your house.

01:17:28.227 --> 01:17:30.228
They told me you was here.

01:17:31.647 --> 01:17:33.982
It's 3:00 a. m., kid.

01:17:35.651 --> 01:17:39.571
That Adrian,
she's a good girl.

01:17:41.657 --> 01:17:44.659
Me, you know, I'm sorry
for both of you.

01:17:48.164 --> 01:17:53.710
Well, ain't nothing I can
do, is there? Except...

01:17:56.422 --> 01:18:01.968
I'd like to tell you something once,
and then I ain't gonna say it again.

01:18:02.053 --> 01:18:05.263
Well, Rocky,
you got another shot.

01:18:05.765 --> 01:18:09.059
It's a second shot at the...

01:18:10.436 --> 01:18:13.938
I don't know, the biggest
title in the world.

01:18:14.940 --> 01:18:18.568
And you're gonna
be swapping punches

01:18:18.652 --> 01:18:22.197
with the most dangerous
fighter in the world.

01:18:23.824 --> 01:18:28.953
And just in case, you know,
your brain ain't working so good,

01:18:30.164 --> 01:18:35.085
all this happens pretty soon.
And you ain't ready.

01:18:37.004 --> 01:18:39.964
You're nowhere near
in shape.

01:18:40.049 --> 01:18:44.344
So, I say, you know,
for God's sake,

01:18:44.428 --> 01:18:48.932
why don't you stand up and fight
this guy hard, like you done before?

01:18:49.016 --> 01:18:51.351
That was beautiful!

01:18:53.521 --> 01:18:56.523
But don't lay down in
front of him like this!

01:18:56.607 --> 01:19:00.777
Like a... I don't know, like
some kind of mongrel or something.

01:19:00.861 --> 01:19:04.406
'Cause he's gonna
kick your face in pieces.

01:19:04.490 --> 01:19:09.369
You know that? That's right. This
guy just don't want to win, you know.

01:19:09.453 --> 01:19:12.497
He wants to bury you.
He wants to humiliate you.

01:19:12.581 --> 01:19:14.582
He wants to prove
to the whole world

01:19:14.667 --> 01:19:19.421
that it was nothing but some kind
of a freak the first time out.

01:19:19.505 --> 01:19:22.507
He said you're
a one-time lucky bum.

01:19:26.011 --> 01:19:29.514
Well, now, I don't...

01:19:30.516 --> 01:19:36.271
I don't want to get mad
in a biblical place like this,

01:19:36.355 --> 01:19:41.067
but I think you're a hell of a lot
more than that, kid. A hell of a lot.

01:19:47.283 --> 01:19:51.161
But, now, wait a minute.
If you want to blow it...

01:19:51.245 --> 01:19:56.166
If you want to blow this thing,
damn it, I'm gonna blow it with you.

01:19:57.585 --> 01:20:02.505
Do you want to stay here? I'll
stay with you. I'll stay with you.

01:20:04.842 --> 01:20:05.967
Yeah.

01:20:09.221 --> 01:20:13.099
I'll stay and pray.
What have I got to lose?

01:20:36.332 --> 01:20:38.666
It's gonna be okay.

01:21:31.470 --> 01:21:36.766
"There ain't no other trail to
the ranch, or no shorter one.

01:21:36.850 --> 01:21:39.978
"'Oh, yes, there is,'
said Marvel.

01:21:40.062 --> 01:21:42.397
"'When I was a kid,
I helped my old man

01:21:42.481 --> 01:21:46.317
"'trail some cattle
up from the border. "'

01:21:46.402 --> 01:21:51.281
Can you hear me, Adrian? Keep
listening. Keep listening.

01:21:53.492 --> 01:21:58.371
"After breakfast, Bruce watched
the party get away on the chase.

01:21:58.455 --> 01:22:02.792
"He saw Cora
and Kay and Bud

01:22:02.876 --> 01:22:07.005
"start up the valley 15
minutes ahead of the others.

01:22:07.089 --> 01:22:09.924
"At the last minute,
the girl... "

01:22:10.009 --> 01:22:14.470
"Replied Olga, 'Buck Mason?
Who is he? '

01:22:17.224 --> 01:22:23.062
"White pointed towards Marvel, who
was leading the horses to the corral. "

01:22:37.536 --> 01:22:40.330
Well, I just wrote this
thing for you, Adrian.

01:22:40.414 --> 01:22:45.668
I don't know. Maybe you'll like it.
I'll just read it to you, 'cause...

01:22:45.753 --> 01:22:49.172
"Remember when we
was on ice skates,

01:22:49.256 --> 01:22:52.800
"and I thought you were
supposed to be great,

01:22:52.885 --> 01:22:56.638
"but I kept giving you lip
and you kept trying to slip,

01:22:56.722 --> 01:22:59.265
"so I could catch you?

01:22:59.350 --> 01:23:04.979
"That was our first date. And
after that every day was great.

01:23:05.064 --> 01:23:09.817
"So now I want you to know
that wherever you go,

01:23:09.902 --> 01:23:15.907
"Atlantic City or in the snow,
don't worry about a thing.

01:23:15.991 --> 01:23:20.953
"'Cause as long as I got this ring,
I'll always be there to catch you. "

01:24:33.694 --> 01:24:35.695
I knew you'd come back.

01:24:45.622 --> 01:24:47.623
Thank you, God.

01:24:51.795 --> 01:24:56.007
Anybody want a refill? Adrian,
it costs six bucks a bottle.

01:24:56.091 --> 01:24:58.050
I don't need that.
I ain't drinking now.

01:24:58.135 --> 01:25:00.011
So, you haven't
seen the baby?

01:25:00.095 --> 01:25:01.596
No, come on. I was waiting
to... I've seen him.

01:25:01.680 --> 01:25:02.930
...see him together.

01:25:03.015 --> 01:25:07.185
Hey, the kid's a winner. He's
got forearms like him, Mickey.

01:25:07.269 --> 01:25:09.353
Here he is now. Look.

01:25:09.438 --> 01:25:10.688
Oh, no.

01:25:12.858 --> 01:25:13.941
There's your mommy.

01:25:14.026 --> 01:25:15.109
Oh, baby!

01:25:18.447 --> 01:25:20.114
Is that it?

01:25:23.494 --> 01:25:25.244
I can't believe it.
He's ours?

01:25:25.329 --> 01:25:26.329
Yeah.

01:25:26.413 --> 01:25:28.456
He's really ours?
Thank you.

01:25:28.540 --> 01:25:32.877
Come on. You done all the work.
Adrian, I can't believe you done this.

01:25:32.961 --> 01:25:34.712
Believe me, we did.

01:25:34.797 --> 01:25:36.464
Oh, no.
He ain't got a name.

01:25:36.548 --> 01:25:38.132
What do you want
to call him?

01:25:38.217 --> 01:25:40.968
Paulie's a great name.

01:25:41.053 --> 01:25:43.930
Yeah,
Paulie's a pretty good name.

01:25:44.014 --> 01:25:45.765
What about after the father?

01:25:45.849 --> 01:25:47.517
Rocky, Jr.?

01:25:47.601 --> 01:25:48.851
Come on. You really want to do that?

01:25:48.936 --> 01:25:50.144
Yes.

01:25:50.229 --> 01:25:54.065
Adrian, he's the best I ever
seen. You really done good.

01:25:55.984 --> 01:25:59.487
You look so tired. Why
don't you go get some sleep?

01:25:59.571 --> 01:26:03.324
Oh, no, no. I feel great. I feel
great. Listen, I been thinking.

01:26:03.408 --> 01:26:06.911
If you don't want me
mixing with Creed no more,

01:26:06.995 --> 01:26:10.665
we'll make out some other
kind of way, you know.

01:26:10.749 --> 01:26:12.625
There's one thing
I want you to do for me.

01:26:12.709 --> 01:26:14.585
What?
Come here.

01:26:15.504 --> 01:26:16.712
What?

01:26:16.797 --> 01:26:17.964
Win.

01:26:20.968 --> 01:26:22.552
Win.

01:26:22.636 --> 01:26:25.096
What are we waiting for?
Take us!

01:27:02.134 --> 01:27:03.759
Faster! Faster!

01:27:06.638 --> 01:27:09.765
Keep moving!
Keep moving! Faster.

01:27:10.684 --> 01:27:13.019
Pick them up!
Pick them up!

01:27:16.523 --> 01:27:19.775
That's it.
That's it. Yeah.

01:27:20.861 --> 01:27:21.986
Speed! Speed!

01:27:22.070 --> 01:27:23.946
Come on! Come on!

01:27:25.240 --> 01:27:26.699
Don't be a slouch.

01:27:26.783 --> 01:27:28.159
Fifty-eight, 59...

01:27:28.243 --> 01:27:29.535
One more!
Come on, man!

01:27:29.620 --> 01:27:31.412
Push. Push.

01:27:31.496 --> 01:27:35.207
Forty-four, 45, 46.
Yeah!

01:27:35.292 --> 01:27:40.004
Forty-seven,
48, 49, 50!

01:27:56.647 --> 01:28:01.400
Again! Again! Now get that out of here!

01:28:01.485 --> 01:28:04.570
Come on! Push!
Don't give up!

01:28:04.655 --> 01:28:06.447
Get that olive oil
out of you!

01:28:07.658 --> 01:28:08.950
Push!

01:28:10.285 --> 01:28:13.037
Twenty-seven, 28...

01:28:16.583 --> 01:28:19.543
Forty-one, 42, 43...

01:28:20.128 --> 01:28:21.754
Forty-six, 47...

01:28:22.339 --> 01:28:24.882
Push! Push!
Again!

01:28:27.970 --> 01:28:29.387
Left! Right!

01:28:38.355 --> 01:28:40.272
Yeah! Yeah!

01:28:40.357 --> 01:28:41.857
Speed!

01:28:45.028 --> 01:28:48.948
Speed!
Speed! Speed!

01:29:11.430 --> 01:29:13.097
Good night.

01:29:34.286 --> 01:29:35.911
Hey, Rocky!

01:29:51.053 --> 01:29:52.720
Hey, Rocky!

01:29:52.804 --> 01:29:54.472
Rocky, you gotta put
him down this time!

01:30:13.283 --> 01:30:15.117
Come on, come on!

01:31:33.572 --> 01:31:35.322
I'm up!

01:31:45.709 --> 01:31:51.755
Rocky! Rocky!

01:32:41.264 --> 01:32:43.891
Good evening, ladies and gentlemen,
this is Bill Baldwin speaking to you

01:32:43.975 --> 01:32:46.227
from the magnificent Spectrum
here in Philadelphia,

01:32:46.311 --> 01:32:47.686
the site of Superfight II,

01:32:47.771 --> 01:32:49.271
with Rocky Balboa,
the challenger,

01:32:49.356 --> 01:32:52.316
and of course Apollo Creed,
the world champion.

01:32:52.400 --> 01:32:55.319
My sidekick and partner
again tonight, Stu Nahan.

01:32:55.403 --> 01:32:58.239
Thank you, Bill, and for those of you
who are watching tonight's telecast,

01:32:58.323 --> 01:33:02.159
we think you're gonna see a real great
battle in every sense of the word.

01:33:06.331 --> 01:33:09.875
Don't worry about nothing.
It's okay.

01:33:14.005 --> 01:33:15.381
I gotta go.

01:33:18.635 --> 01:33:22.012
Adrian, I wish the doctor
would let you go to this fight.

01:33:22.847 --> 01:33:24.014
Me, too.

01:33:25.183 --> 01:33:29.103
You're the man. You're number one.
The champ. The best of all time.

01:33:29.187 --> 01:33:31.772
The girls love you.
Men, old people love you.

01:33:31.856 --> 01:33:34.692
Young people love you. You're
the best. You're the man.

01:33:34.776 --> 01:33:37.152
And he's yours. He's yours. He's yours.

01:33:37.237 --> 01:33:39.780
This bum shouldn't even be
in the same ring with you.

01:33:39.864 --> 01:33:41.699
I want you to show him
who you are tonight.

01:33:41.783 --> 01:33:44.285
Show him who you are
tonight. Stick him.

01:33:44.661 --> 01:33:46.328
Go, Rocky, go!

01:33:55.380 --> 01:33:58.007
Now, listen, Paulie, you're gonna
help out with the baby tonight, right?

01:33:58.091 --> 01:33:59.133
I'll take care
of everything.

01:33:59.217 --> 01:34:01.468
Okay, you just take care of everything
now because you're in charge.

01:34:01.553 --> 01:34:04.096
I'll take care of the dumb house.
You're gonna be late for your own fight.

01:34:04.180 --> 01:34:05.681
Everything's gonna
be fine.

01:34:05.765 --> 01:34:08.350
Well, maybe I'd
better go fight now.

01:34:08.435 --> 01:34:09.893
I love you.

01:34:09.978 --> 01:34:11.395
I love you, too.

01:34:11.479 --> 01:34:12.646
Punch his lungs out.

01:34:12.731 --> 01:34:14.315
Adrian,
I wish you could go.

01:34:14.399 --> 01:34:15.816
The doctor said no.

01:34:15.900 --> 01:34:17.192
I got
the doctor's instructions.

01:34:17.277 --> 01:34:19.153
Take care.
Good luck.

01:34:35.086 --> 01:34:38.130
The champion has let it be
known to the press and radio

01:34:38.214 --> 01:34:41.258
that he is in the best shape
of his illustrious career.

01:34:44.971 --> 01:34:47.473
And Rocky Balboa, I know,
is a 5-to-1 underdog.

01:34:47.557 --> 01:34:50.184
I know he's still a street
brawler from Philadelphia.

01:34:50.268 --> 01:34:53.312
But can he repeat that incredible
performance of 10 months ago?

01:34:53.396 --> 01:34:57.524
And, you know, he took a real
beating at the hands of the champion.

01:34:59.778 --> 01:35:01.028
Carmine!

01:35:02.697 --> 01:35:06.200
Hey, yo, Father Carmine!
Father Carmine!

01:35:06.284 --> 01:35:08.327
Hey, Father Carmine,
are you home?

01:35:08.411 --> 01:35:11.288
Father Carmine!
Hey, yo, Father Carmine!

01:35:12.457 --> 01:35:14.750
It's me, Rocky Balboa.

01:35:14.834 --> 01:35:16.168
Rocky?
Yeah.

01:35:19.798 --> 01:35:21.548
Oh, yeah, I'm going
to the fight right now,

01:35:21.633 --> 01:35:24.551
but I was wondering if you could
do me a small favor, you know.

01:35:26.137 --> 01:35:27.388
Well, it's about the fight,
you know?

01:35:27.472 --> 01:35:29.556
Now I got the family and
the baby and all that stuff.

01:35:29.641 --> 01:35:32.434
And I was wondering, you know, if
you could throw down a blessing,

01:35:32.519 --> 01:35:36.772
so that if I get beat up tonight, you
know, it won't be too bad, you know?

01:35:36.856 --> 01:35:39.274
Could you do
something like that?

01:35:44.447 --> 01:35:47.116
Thanks a lot, Father. Listen, I
appreciate it. I gotta go. I'm so late.

01:35:47.200 --> 01:35:49.660
I'll see you in church,
I hope. Take care.

01:36:09.222 --> 01:36:10.389
Hey, Rock.

01:36:10.473 --> 01:36:11.640
Good luck, son.

01:36:11.891 --> 01:36:14.268
Yo, Mick! Run, or I'll break your head!

01:36:14.352 --> 01:36:16.478
Where you been? You lost
your brain or something?

01:36:16.563 --> 01:36:17.771
We got a fight,
remember that?

01:36:17.856 --> 01:36:19.440
I'm sorry. I'm here.

01:36:19.524 --> 01:36:21.984
Get dressed, will you?
There's a million people...

01:36:22.068 --> 01:36:24.403
Stu, there are many rumors
circulating about this fight.

01:36:24.487 --> 01:36:28.365
Well, the most obvious being a definite
desire for Apollo to draw first blood,

01:36:28.450 --> 01:36:29.575
to end it quickly.

01:36:29.659 --> 01:36:32.911
This would prove his claim
that the last fight was a fluke.

01:36:32.996 --> 01:36:36.165
Come on, lightning hands!
Hurricane! Hurricane!

01:36:43.214 --> 01:36:45.048
Get him. Get him.
I'm gonna get him.

01:36:45.175 --> 01:36:46.925
Gonna get him. Gonna get
him. He's ours! He's ours!

01:36:47.010 --> 01:36:48.218
Gonna get him.
He's ours! He's ours!

01:36:52.640 --> 01:36:53.682
It's time, kid.

01:37:01.900 --> 01:37:03.567
Okay, let's do it.

01:37:04.402 --> 01:37:06.236
All right, I'm ready.

01:37:12.243 --> 01:37:14.369
You know, I think I'm starting
to get a headache here.

01:37:14.454 --> 01:37:16.955
No, you are in
perfect working condition.

01:37:17.040 --> 01:37:18.999
You are perfect.
Yeah, you look good, too.

01:37:19.083 --> 01:37:21.543
Yeah, thanks. And you
look perfect. Perfect.

01:37:21.628 --> 01:37:23.337
Hey, Mick. Hey, Mick.
Yeah. Yeah.

01:37:23.421 --> 01:37:24.630
In case I don't get a chance,

01:37:24.714 --> 01:37:27.925
I just want to say I'm gonna be
trying hard for you today, okay?

01:37:28.009 --> 01:37:29.927
Thank you.

01:37:30.011 --> 01:37:31.595
Ain't this robe nice?

01:37:31.679 --> 01:37:33.180
It's better than last year,
that's for sure.

01:37:33.264 --> 01:37:34.348
Remember that
baggy one last year?

01:37:34.432 --> 01:37:36.183
This is gorgeous.
It's perfect.

01:37:36.267 --> 01:37:37.726
Yeah, it's real cute.
I like it.

01:37:37.810 --> 01:37:39.436
Yeah. Okay.

01:37:44.442 --> 01:37:47.194
Yes, Rocky Balboa
heading toward the ring now.

01:37:47.278 --> 01:37:51.198
Yes, sir. Rocky Balboa, known to
millions as the Italian Stallion,

01:37:51.282 --> 01:37:55.035
making his way to the ring. Why
this fighter of limited ability

01:37:55.119 --> 01:37:58.288
has gained such popularity
is such a mystery.

01:37:58.373 --> 01:38:01.291
Rocky Balboa, and the
folks here at the Spectrum

01:38:01.376 --> 01:38:03.293
are beginning to
chant his name.

01:38:03.378 --> 01:38:05.712
He has an awful
lot of backers here.

01:38:05.797 --> 01:38:08.507
Balboa is wearing
a black and gold robe.

01:38:08.591 --> 01:38:12.219
He wore a red one the last time
from that meat-packing plant.

01:38:12.303 --> 01:38:15.138
Some said that was from the high
school that he never graduated from.

01:38:15.223 --> 01:38:16.265
31 years of age.

01:38:16.349 --> 01:38:19.643
There he is over shaking hands
with the referee, Lou Filippo.

01:38:19.727 --> 01:38:22.312
And we're waiting now for the
champion to come into the ring.

01:38:23.064 --> 01:38:25.357
Rocky! Rocky!

01:38:25.441 --> 01:38:27.734
Rocky! Rocky!

01:38:27.819 --> 01:38:30.112
This area is certainly packed
with Rocky's people.

01:38:30.196 --> 01:38:33.240
I've never seen so many
Italians in one place in my life!

01:38:33.324 --> 01:38:34.908
Hey, hey. You said that.
I didn't say that.

01:38:34.993 --> 01:38:35.993
Rocky! Rocky!
Rocky! Rocky!

01:38:36.077 --> 01:38:38.078
These people are for you,
Rock! I appreciate it.

01:38:38.162 --> 01:38:39.204
Are you ready
in here?

01:38:39.289 --> 01:38:40.247
I think so.

01:38:40.331 --> 01:38:42.249
Yeah, well, tonight's
our night, kid.

01:38:42.333 --> 01:38:46.420
By the sound of the crowd, the champion
is just now coming into the Spectrum.

01:38:46.504 --> 01:38:48.755
And the champion,
Apollo Creed.

01:38:48.840 --> 01:38:53.343
And he looks a little more determined
this time than he did the last time.

01:38:53.428 --> 01:38:55.304
It's Apollo.
Who'd you expect?

01:38:55.388 --> 01:38:57.639
I was hoping
he wouldn't show.

01:39:01.686 --> 01:39:03.937
The champ
of all time!

01:39:04.022 --> 01:39:06.273
Now the champion is
climbing into the ring.

01:39:06.357 --> 01:39:10.068
Very determined-looking.
Very serious right now.

01:39:10.278 --> 01:39:12.112
Rocky doesn't look as
confident as he might.

01:39:12.196 --> 01:39:17.743
Apollo Creed, the master of
disaster, the best of all time!

01:39:21.414 --> 01:39:24.207
You're going down, man.
You're going down.

01:39:25.168 --> 01:39:27.252
Don't let it bother you,
kid.

01:39:27.378 --> 01:39:28.670
Would it bother you?

01:39:28.713 --> 01:39:29.755
Yeah.

01:39:29.839 --> 01:39:32.716
Good evening,
ladies and gentlemen,

01:39:32.800 --> 01:39:36.219
and welcome to
the Philadelphia Spectrum!

01:39:38.056 --> 01:39:41.266
This is your main
event of the evening,

01:39:41.351 --> 01:39:46.355
15 rounds for the heavyweight
championship of the world!

01:39:50.568 --> 01:39:57.449
In the black corner, the
challenger, weighing 202 pounds,

01:39:57.533 --> 01:40:01.286
from the great fighting city
of Philadelphia,

01:40:01.371 --> 01:40:06.875
the Italian Stallion,
Rocky Balboa!

01:40:18.429 --> 01:40:23.684
And in the red corner,
weighing 220 pounds,

01:40:23.768 --> 01:40:29.189
a champion who needs no introduction
anywhere in the civilized world,

01:40:29.273 --> 01:40:32.401
the true master of disaster,

01:40:32.485 --> 01:40:36.697
the undefeated heavyweight
champion of the world,

01:40:36.781 --> 01:40:43.120
the one, the only,
Apollo Creed!

01:40:47.917 --> 01:40:51.336
Referee Lou Filippo
will give the instructions.

01:41:01.264 --> 01:41:04.558
Okay, boys, I'm gonna give
you the instructions now,

01:41:04.642 --> 01:41:06.143
and I expect you
to follow them.

01:41:06.227 --> 01:41:09.563
Watch your low punches and
watch your kidney punches.

01:41:09.647 --> 01:41:10.856
Watch your
rabbit punches.

01:41:10.940 --> 01:41:13.400
In case of a knockdown, you
go to the corner I tell you to

01:41:13.484 --> 01:41:15.902
and stay there until I tell
you to come out, understand?

01:41:15.987 --> 01:41:18.572
Okay, boys. Let's have
a good fight.

01:41:20.158 --> 01:41:21.825
You're going down.

01:41:23.161 --> 01:41:24.953
You can do it, Rocky!

01:41:25.121 --> 01:41:26.872
Good luck to you.

01:41:28.791 --> 01:41:29.833
He's still upset.

01:41:29.917 --> 01:41:31.752
Who cares? Now, listen,
protect that eye.

01:41:31.836 --> 01:41:35.422
And no matter what happens, don't go
back to fighting southpaw till I tell you.

01:41:35.506 --> 01:41:37.174
Now, you get him.
Okay.

01:41:37.258 --> 01:41:38.383
Good luck.

01:41:38.468 --> 01:41:39.509
Now he's gonna try
to kill you quick.

01:41:39.594 --> 01:41:42.387
If you get through this
first round, then he's ours.

01:41:42.513 --> 01:41:44.473
Okay. Show him who you are.

01:41:50.480 --> 01:41:54.399
As Rocky Balboa prays in his corner,
the champion dancing over in his corner,

01:41:54.484 --> 01:41:56.902
we're just seconds away from the
fight of the century, Superfight II.

01:41:58.070 --> 01:41:59.321
And there's the bell.

01:42:00.698 --> 01:42:02.574
And the champion
comes over in a hurry now,

01:42:02.658 --> 01:42:04.618
and throws a couple of
rights and lefts out there.

01:42:04.702 --> 01:42:06.578
He starts to take
command early here.

01:42:06.662 --> 01:42:10.499
And now, he kind of moves his feet
along the side of the ring now.

01:42:10.583 --> 01:42:13.502
Rocky's holding that right
hand. He's fighting right-handed!

01:42:13.586 --> 01:42:18.048
I don't believe it. The southpaw
from Philly is fighting right-handed!

01:42:21.052 --> 01:42:34.523
Rocky! Rocky!

01:42:34.607 --> 01:42:37.651
Break that damn jab!
Protect that eye!

01:42:40.988 --> 01:42:42.405
Is that all you got?
Is that all you got?

01:42:42.490 --> 01:42:43.865
Break it up there.

01:42:43.950 --> 01:42:45.158
You ain't got nothing.

01:42:45.243 --> 01:42:46.451
Break it up.

01:42:46.577 --> 01:42:47.994
You ready to
lay down?

01:42:48.079 --> 01:42:50.872
A good right hand followed by
another right and another right

01:42:50.957 --> 01:42:52.082
thrown by the champion.

01:42:52.166 --> 01:42:55.001
Three good right
hands bang at Balboa.

01:42:55.086 --> 01:42:57.003
They're in the corner,
and there's left to right.

01:42:57.088 --> 01:42:59.005
Here comes Balboa
coming back at him.

01:42:59.090 --> 01:43:01.842
A left and a right to the head,
and now back off of the ropes.

01:43:01.926 --> 01:43:03.677
Balboa appears to
be getting hit often,

01:43:03.761 --> 01:43:06.555
but he seems to be
in pretty good condition.

01:43:06.639 --> 01:43:09.599
A hard right hand thrown by
the champion. Another right.

01:43:09.684 --> 01:43:12.394
Balboa is in trouble now.
He's in trouble.

01:43:12.478 --> 01:43:16.022
Taking rights and lefts as
the champion begins to open up.

01:43:16.107 --> 01:43:19.150
It was a tremendous
right hand. Balboa is down!

01:43:19.235 --> 01:43:21.236
Down goes Balboa!

01:43:21.946 --> 01:43:23.321
Get back.

01:43:23.573 --> 01:43:27.409
We see Apollo hit that bad left
eye, remember, from the first fight.

01:43:27.493 --> 01:43:30.620
That's the eye that was cut the last
time. Balboa getting up rather unsteadily.

01:43:30.705 --> 01:43:31.872
Go get him!

01:43:31.956 --> 01:43:34.207
Go after him, kid!
Go after him!

01:43:34.292 --> 01:43:35.292
Yeah.

01:43:36.752 --> 01:43:40.255
And the champion starts to move
in again. Going right, left.

01:43:40.339 --> 01:43:44.718
He's taking those punches pretty well.
And now Balboa just comes right back!

01:43:44.802 --> 01:43:46.469
Tossed the ref right
into the ring post.

01:43:46.554 --> 01:43:48.847
Coming out now,
he wants at him.

01:43:48.931 --> 01:43:52.392
Balboa's tagged. Left, left, and
right combinations by the champion.

01:43:52.476 --> 01:43:55.729
Another left. He's leaning
back, but there's the bell!

01:43:55.813 --> 01:43:57.355
There's the end
of the round.

01:44:00.318 --> 01:44:03.153
There's a lot of
bad blood between these two.

01:44:03.946 --> 01:44:05.572
Good round.
Good round.

01:44:05.656 --> 01:44:06.990
I can't believe it.
What?

01:44:07.074 --> 01:44:08.742
He broke my nose again.

01:44:08.826 --> 01:44:11.912
Balboa has gotta be in great
shape to withstand that butchery.

01:44:11.996 --> 01:44:15.415
Man, I'll tell you, that's just
what it is. It's plain old butchery.

01:44:15.833 --> 01:44:17.542
Did the switching bother
you? Nothing bothered me.

01:44:17.627 --> 01:44:18.752
All right, but then you
should have had him.

01:44:18.836 --> 01:44:20.420
You can't be hurt.

01:44:20.504 --> 01:44:22.881
You follow? You can't be
hurt, 'cause you are too tough.

01:44:22.965 --> 01:44:25.300
Now don't let up on this man.
This man is dangerous.

01:44:25.384 --> 01:44:26.801
This man is dangerous?
I'm dangerous.

01:44:26.886 --> 01:44:28.261
The man is dangerous.

01:44:28.346 --> 01:44:29.804
That guy is great.

01:44:29.889 --> 01:44:31.348
No. Listen,
he's only a man.

01:44:31.432 --> 01:44:34.351
You can beat him
because you're a tank.

01:44:34.518 --> 01:44:38.063
You're a greasy, fast,
200-pound Italian tank.

01:44:38.147 --> 01:44:40.273
Go through him!
Run over him!

01:44:40.358 --> 01:44:42.484
I'm a tank.
I'm gonna get him.

01:44:43.069 --> 01:44:44.986
This is it, man!
The best of all time!

01:44:45.071 --> 01:44:46.488
Here we go.
Round two.

01:44:47.448 --> 01:44:50.325
Round two. The champion comes back
out. He's leaning across again.

01:44:50.409 --> 01:44:52.160
Starting with a left
and a left and a left.

01:44:52.244 --> 01:44:54.955
Left to the chin, left to the head.
Left to the chin, left to the head.

01:44:55.039 --> 01:44:56.790
Coming around now.
Just holding that right hand.

01:44:56.874 --> 01:44:57.999
He's got it cocked.

01:44:58.084 --> 01:45:00.377
He's just waiting for that
precise moment that he wants to...

01:45:00.461 --> 01:45:03.296
There it is! He unloaded
that, but here comes Balboa!

01:45:06.592 --> 01:45:08.677
You can't hurt me. He
can't hurt me! No way!

01:45:08.761 --> 01:45:11.054
Break it up.
Break it up.

01:45:12.473 --> 01:45:13.807
Break it up.
Break clean.

01:45:13.891 --> 01:45:15.225
Come on, come on.

01:45:16.394 --> 01:45:19.062
You're too slow!
Man, you're too slow!

01:45:20.064 --> 01:45:24.275
Get your cameras ready. Watch this
now. Watch this. He's going down.

01:45:25.903 --> 01:45:27.612
Here it comes!

01:45:35.121 --> 01:45:36.121
Down he goes!

01:45:36.247 --> 01:45:37.414
Rocky!

01:45:37.498 --> 01:45:39.416
Get up, Rock! Get up!

01:45:39.500 --> 01:45:43.253
Balboa for the second time
is down, struggling to get up.

01:45:43.796 --> 01:45:47.382
Don't get up. Just stay down
there. Just stay down there, chump!

01:45:47.466 --> 01:45:48.466
I told you!

01:45:48.551 --> 01:45:49.509
Beautiful!

01:45:49.593 --> 01:45:52.679
Six,
seven, eight...

01:45:52.763 --> 01:45:55.265
Protect that eye, kid!
Get at it!

01:45:55.349 --> 01:45:56.933
The body, the body, the body!
You're a tank, kid!

01:45:57.018 --> 01:45:58.476
Let's go, Rock.
Yeah.

01:45:58.561 --> 01:46:00.437
I told you! I told you!

01:46:03.232 --> 01:46:04.649
And here comes
the champion...

01:46:04.734 --> 01:46:06.026
One, two, now.
One, two.

01:46:06.110 --> 01:46:08.695
Here it is. A left and a right and
he's got him back in the corner!

01:46:08.779 --> 01:46:10.113
Balboa's back in the corner!

01:46:10.197 --> 01:46:13.491
But here comes Balboa again!
Where does he get that stamina?

01:46:13.576 --> 01:46:15.702
He's got the champion
trapped in the corner.

01:46:15.786 --> 01:46:18.580
And he's breaking
left and right, left...

01:46:18.664 --> 01:46:26.713
Rocky! Rocky!

01:46:32.261 --> 01:46:33.678
Keep it up! Keep it up!

01:46:38.142 --> 01:46:39.559
I'm standing here.

01:46:39.643 --> 01:46:42.145
A great second round. And
they're taunting each other.

01:46:42.229 --> 01:46:45.648
The bell, the round is over,
but they're taunting each other.

01:46:45.733 --> 01:46:49.110
Everybody in the audience better
get ready for World War III.

01:46:51.322 --> 01:46:53.698
I ain't going down
no more.

01:46:53.908 --> 01:46:56.076
Attaboy! Go get him!

01:47:09.215 --> 01:47:10.673
Come on, kid!

01:47:13.511 --> 01:47:14.844
Come on,
break it up!

01:47:17.389 --> 01:47:18.431
And the champion
again

01:47:18.516 --> 01:47:22.143
with a combination of lefts
and rights to the head.

01:47:24.105 --> 01:47:25.438
That was another
round for Creed.

01:47:25.523 --> 01:47:28.233
Creed keeps piling
up the points, but...

01:47:28.317 --> 01:47:29.567
Get him, Rock.

01:47:37.827 --> 01:47:38.868
Hit him! Just hit him!

01:47:44.041 --> 01:47:46.501
Another round
for Apollo Creed.

01:47:56.929 --> 01:47:59.097
Here comes Balboa
again into the corner.

01:47:59.181 --> 01:48:01.724
Lefts and rights to the
midsection, and those hurt.

01:48:07.231 --> 01:48:09.232
Pound
the body!

01:48:09.608 --> 01:48:11.359
He's won
another round.

01:48:11.485 --> 01:48:13.236
He now begins to
taunt Balboa again.

01:48:14.613 --> 01:48:15.905
Come on!

01:48:43.767 --> 01:48:45.768
I'm gonna give
that round to Balboa.

01:48:45.853 --> 01:48:49.022
You wonder what's on Apollo
Creed's mind right now.

01:48:49.106 --> 01:48:51.191
He's lost his first round.

01:48:57.239 --> 01:48:58.823
Go for it, Rock!

01:49:06.957 --> 01:49:09.375
Balboa is on his way.

01:49:14.840 --> 01:49:17.884
Hands up! Hands up!
Now, just stick and move!

01:49:17.968 --> 01:49:20.386
This man is breaking you up
inside! Now, stick and move!

01:49:20.471 --> 01:49:21.846
Keep your hands up!

01:49:22.806 --> 01:49:24.724
Lightning! Thunder!

01:49:42.660 --> 01:49:44.035
Hit him back!

01:49:47.915 --> 01:49:52.669
I thought he took a beating 10 months
ago, Stu, but tonight it's twice as bad!

01:49:54.171 --> 01:49:57.382
Another round for the
champion, Apollo Creed.

01:49:59.426 --> 01:50:01.761
The left eye is closed.
Now bust him, understand?

01:50:01.845 --> 01:50:03.012
Keep working on him.

01:50:04.890 --> 01:50:06.099
Stay away from him.

01:50:06.183 --> 01:50:08.268
Don't let him breathe!
Get him!

01:50:24.868 --> 01:50:27.870
Balboa's taking another
beating in the corner.

01:50:29.581 --> 01:50:31.916
Another round
for the champion.

01:51:09.705 --> 01:51:11.497
Now come on!
You got him beat on points.

01:51:11.582 --> 01:51:12.915
You understand?
Now, stick and move!

01:51:13.000 --> 01:51:14.083
Don't go for
the knockout!

01:51:14.168 --> 01:51:15.209
He's gonna fall.
He's gonna fall.

01:51:15.294 --> 01:51:18.212
Don't go for the knockout, you understand!
